title: molasses crinkles
directions: Chill dough about an hour.
Form into balls.
Dip top half in water; roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple-lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add cream cheese.
Mix until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: cauliflower medley
directions: Wash and cut into pieces the cauliflower and broccoli.
Cook in a saucepan in salted water until almost tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add butter and lemon juice; cook until butter melts. Remove from heat.
Stir in tomatoes and serve.

title: puffy crab canapes
directions: Combine
crab, celery, mustard, salt and 3/4 cup mayonnaise and
mix
well.
Lightly toast muffins, which have been spread with butter and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form
and fold in 3 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Spoon crab mixture on
muffins,
which
have
been
quartered.
Top with beaten
egg mixture and spread to cover filling.
Bake at 450° for about 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24 servings.

title: potato fudge candy
directions: Mix all together.
Drop onto a waxed paper lined cookie sheet and form into a mound.
Place in icebox to harden.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of candy and stays moist for days.

title: hot tuna biscuits
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
Preheat oven to 425°.
Pat each biscuit into a thin, 4-inch oval.
Arrange half of biscuits on greased cookie sheet.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all together and make into walnut-size balls.
If made too large, the sauce won't cook through to flavor.
Place in a flat pan in a single layer touching each other.
(Pan needs to be larger than 9 x 13-inches).
They are really moist.
Can be frozen for future use.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix vegetables with chicken and soup. Place in ungreased 9-inch pie pan. Mix Bisquick milk and egg until smooth. Pour into pie pan. Bake 30 minutes or until brown.

title: marinated cucumbers and tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: taco dish
directions: Bring soup and milk to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Put Fritos and other ingredients in layers.
Pour soup-milk mixture over Fritos.
Bake at 400°.

title: lemon frozen yogurt
directions: In a 9 to 10-inch square metal pan, mix yogurt, lemon peel, lemon juice and corn syrup.
Cover airtight and freeze until firm, at least 6 hours or up to 3 weeks.
Break frozen mixture into large chunks.
If too hard, let stand a few minutes at room temperature to soften.
Whirl chunks in food processor or beat with a mixer until a smooth textured slush forms.
Return slush mixture to pan.
Cover and freeze until firmed slightly, 30 minutes to 3 hours.
Scoop frozen yogurt into chilled bowls; decorate with lemon slices.

title: chinese noodles
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on a buttered cookie sheet.

title: green chile quesadillas
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cheese, chiles, corn and green onions.
Spread 1/3 c. cheese mixture onto one half of each tortilla and fold tortilla in half.
Spray a large skillet with nonstick cooking spray and place 2 quesadillas at a time in the skillet.
Cook each side over medium heat until tortilla is golden brown and cheese is melted.
Repeat with remaining ingredients. Cut each quesadilla in half and serve with salsa and cilantro. Makes 10.

title: vegetable-beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet, stirring to crumble. Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Set sauce aside. Layer half of the beef, potatoes, onions, peas and sauce in a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, for an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: supper on bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Slice loaf in half lengthwise.
Spread meat mixture over top.
Wrap foil around crust, leaving top uncovered.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian pasta and veggie skillet
directions: Cook pasta according to pkg. directions.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle sugar over onion; continue cooking until onion is caramelized and golden, about 5 minutes. Add bell pepper, mushrooms, garlic and pasta sauce.
Add drained pasta to skillet tossing to coat.
Transfer to serving plates; top with cheese and basil.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly sausage, cheese and Bisquick. Shape into small balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: About 75.

title: sausage cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 3-quart baking dish.
Bring water and salt to a boil.
Slowly stir in grits and cook until done.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and butter until melted.
Add eggs, milk and sausage.
Blend well.
Pour mixture into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake for 1 hour, until set.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: tomato relish
directions: Grind the first 5 ingredients through a coarse grinder. Soak mixture overnight
in
plain salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Wash excess salt off.
Add
vinegar and brown sugar.
Place mustard seed in a small cheesecloth bag.
Cook vinegar and ingredients slowly, 1 hour.
Remove
spice
bag.
Makes approximately 8 to 12 pints.

title: peanut butter fudge 1
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter together until they reach the soft ball stage; add vanilla, salt and peanut butter; beat.
Pour in 8-inch square buttered pan and cool.

title: summer cheese ball
directions: Mix all above with 1 cup of the pecans.
Refrigerate one hour and then form into a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: baked hand pies
directions: Let biscuits set out for a few minutes before rolling out. Then roll out on floured surface.
Roll out 1 biscuit per pie.
To cook apples, add cinnamon and sugar in apples, then spread apples on rolled out biscuit.
Fold over, brush with oil, dip fork in flour and press around edge of pie.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 10 minutes or brown.
Yields 20 pies.

title: caramels
directions: In heavy saucepan melt butter.
Add corn syrup and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add 1 1/2 cans of milk.
Mix flour with rest of milk.
Add to syrup mixture. Boil until darkens and forms medium hard ball (240°).
Stir constantly or mixture will stick.
Add vanilla and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 2 regular size muffin pans or mini muffin pans with paper liners or grease pans and sprinkle lightly with flour.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Cream the butter. Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.

Add flour mixture alternately with milk. Beat well after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Fill prepared pans 2/3 of the way full with mixture. Bake until done, approximately 20 minutes for large muffins and 12 to 15 minutes for small.

title: cherry winks cookies
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Combine and cream well the shortening and sugar.
Add and beat well the eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix well and add pecans, dates and 1/3 cup chopped cherries.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Wash and peel raw shrimp and remove black veins.
Heat shortening in deep skillet.
Add flour and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until rich dark brown.
Add chopped onions, celery, green peppers, tomato sauce and water.
Let simmer 30 minutes and bring to boiling.
Add shrimp and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt, and vanilla. Stir in flour and oats.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate evenly when melted.
Drizzle topping over chocolate.
Cool.
Cut into fingers or bars.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet in cooking oil until well browned.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Add rice, water and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring frequently.
(If rice does not seem to be cooking thoroughly through this process, continue adding water in small amounts until cooked.)
Add green onions and parsley just before serving.

title: almond tea ring
directions: Mix yeast
and warm water.
Place All-Bran, scalded milk, shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in mixing bowl until lukewarm. Add yeast mixture, eggs, flavor and 2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour and mix thoroughly.
Knead 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and allow to raise until double
(2 hours).
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll each 22 x 1/4-inch thick.
Spread
with oleo; sprinkle with sugar and nuts.
Roll tightly and press
edge together.
Place on greased sheet in a circle. Cut diagonally with
shears
at
1-inch
intervals,
turning
each cut slightly. Let raise until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Glaze with 10x sugar
frosting
and
top
with
maraschino
cherries and more almonds.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat thoroughly sugar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing in order given.
Line pans with wax paper; otherwise, it sticks badly.
Bake in 3 layers or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Put rhubarb in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Cream sugar, salt and butter or margarine.
Add milk alternately with flour mixture and vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Cook meat and drain; heat chili.
Dip tortilla shells in chili and line the bottom of pan.
Put a layer of meat, then chili, then cheese.
Repeat.
Heat in 350° to 375° oven until cheese is melted. Serve with chips.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces, add orange juice, pineapple, sugar and salt.
Cook slowly to thickness desired.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine vegies, soup, 1/2 cup of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can of the onions.
Pour into a shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on the top and put back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix; beat vigorously.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and 1 teaspoon garlic powder.
Brush on biscuits after baking.
Makes 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except pie filling.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pie filling and put rest of flour-oats mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: walnut clusters
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a small mixin bowl, stir together the whole wheat flour and baking soda; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the peanut butter and margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium speed for about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add the sugar and vanilla, beating until well combined.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each addition.
Stir in the chunk-style applesauce.
Then, add the flour mixture to the peanut butter mixture, stirring, until well blended.
Stir in the rolled oats and wheat germ.

title: fried cheese sticks
directions: Slice very cold Mozzarella in cubes or sticks; dip in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.
Dip back in egg and bread crumbs again, being sure cheese is well covered.
Fry in oil in deep fryer a few at a time, turning once until golden.

title: feather gingerbread
directions: Beat all ingredients in large bowl 3 minutes.
Pour in well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serve warm with applesauce and whipped cream.

title: graham cracker balls
directions: Mix everything except oleo, adding it last.
Make tiny balls. Refrigerate balls for 15 minutes.
Melt 1/4 pound of paraffin wax and add 1 small package chocolate chips in a deep boiler.
Dip balls, using toothpick for dipping.
Makes about 75 balls.

title: hashed brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
Spread cheese on top when about ready, until cheese melts.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain good.
Place vegetables, tomatoes, broth and meat mixture in large pot.
Bring to boil and simmer until thick.

title: potato soup
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp. Remove and set aside. Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of fat. Add onions and brown. Add potatoes and enough water to cover. Cook until tender (15 to 20 minutes). Combine soup and milk; stir until smooth and add to potato mix. Heat but do not boil. Add salt and pepper to taste. Crumble bacon and add just before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and apple juice.
Chill, but don't set.
Mix cranberries and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients. Using a large casserole dish, add second mixture to first mixture, then add third mixture.

title: hot oyster soup
directions: Put in a 6-quart saucepan.
Heat until steaming hot.
Serve with round or soda crackers.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer.
Serve with green salad and French bread for a nice supper.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake for 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: east texas fried chicken with hickory nut gravy
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and dip in buttermilk. Roll in flour. Drop in deep fat and fry until done. Set aside.
Drain off most of fat, leaving about 1 cup in bottom of pan. Add flour and cornstarch.
Keep pan hot and stir until brown and bubbly, then add condensed milk and hot water.
Stir constantly until mixture begins to thicken. Add hickory nut meats.
Gradually stir in homogenized milk and beer.
Add peppers and salt to taste.
Cook down to desired thickness.

title: simple marinara sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oil and saut garlic, onion and rosemary.
Add tomatoes and their juice.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to gentle boil, uncovered, for about 10 minutes. Add basil.
Cover and let stand for at least 30 minutes.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix dry jello and strawberries together; bring to a boil. Cool until slightly set.
Mix milk and pudding.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Alternate layers of vanilla wafers (crumbled), strawberry mix and pudding mixture.
Top with vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Make the night before and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, marshmallows, pineapple and pecans.
Stir in dry pudding mix last.
Keep refrigerated.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Dice boiled potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes.
Serves approximately 15.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix well.
Keeps in refrigerator well for 2 weeks.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine margarine, sugars and pudding mix in a large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; then stir in oats and raisins (batter will be stiff).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cooking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350 degrees for one hour.
(Knife inserted comes out clean.)

title: party punch
directions: Mix all the juices at least three hours before using to blend the flavors.
Pour in the ginger ale just before serving.
Add sherbet.
Serves approximately 30.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together in saucepan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, quick oatmeal and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: Beat the egg whites until they form a soft peak.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar and beat just until blended.
Put in refrigerator until needed.
Cream shortening and 2 cups of sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternating with the milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Add hot water last with vanilla.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Shape into balls.
Brown and make a gravy from the drippings. These are the meatballs that we make for our annual meetings.

title: breakfast granola
directions: Spread rolled oats on a 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Toast in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine honey and vegetable oil in a saucepan.
Heat but do not boil.
Stir in vanilla. Remove oats from oven.
Toss with nuts, bran, coconut and sunflower seeds.
Pour hot honey mixture over oat mixture.
Toss well.
Return to oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring 3 to 4 times while baking.
Remove from oven; add raisins and dates. Stir well.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, vanilla, eggs, half and half and sugar.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar and flour and then mix with 1 1/2 cups broken pecans and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: honey brown bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Scald milk, and add butter, salt, and honey.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast mixture.
Add white flour and whole wheat flour, a cup at a time. Knead until dough is elastic and shiny.
Let rise in a warm place until double.
Punch down and shape into loaves.
Let rise to the top of the pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Put sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, nuts and oatmeal. Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper and let cool.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Stir by hand until well mixed.
Cook in greased 12-cup Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool before taking out of pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions, pepper and mushrooms, stirring until browned.
Mix in cream and flour into smooth consistency on low heat.
Stir in ham.
Remove from heat.
Stir in egg and parsley.
Return to heat that is very low and stir until thick.
Pour over cooked and drained Colavita A Nido noodles.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Melt butter and saute all ingredients, except cheese, in a covered skillet for 5 to 10 minutes until zucchini is tender. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand until cheese melts. Serve immediately.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: debbie's cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses until well blended.
Add rest of ingredients. Form 2 even balls. Cover with nuts.

title: bertha's dip
directions: Combine cheese and ham.
Form into a ball and press nuts on outside.

title: carrot-raisin muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flours, sugar, ginger, cinnamon and baking powder. Make well in center and set aside. In small mixing bowl, stir together beaten eggs, undrained pineapple, carrots, raisins, corn syrup and vanilla. Add all at once to flour mixture. Stir just until moist. Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups. Divide batter and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Drain and rinse black-eyed peas.
Put in mixing bowl. Add chopped vegetables.
Stir in Italian salad dressing to taste.

title: mocha-walnut christmas cookies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup morsels over hot boiling water.
Stir until smooth and cool to room temperature.
In
a cup, dissolve instant coffee in boiling water.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and coffee.
Heat until creamy.
Add egg and melted chocolate.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 24 (3-inch) cookies.

title: lemon lust
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press in the bottom of oblong pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix milk with pudding.
Spread on cheese layer.
Spread thin layer Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.
Serves 15.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Heat soup; add gelatin softened in cold water.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Pour into molds; chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: canned apples or peaches for pies
directions: Cook until thick and can.

title: lite cherry delight
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and butter thoroughly.
Press into pan. Chill.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk and blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with cherries.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Put into 10 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm Herb Dressing mixed with 2/3 stick margarine. Serves 10 to 12 people generously.

title: wilted lettuce and onion salad
directions: Heat to boiling point and pour over 1 1/2 quarts shredded lettuce and 3 chopped green onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Toss to mix.
Serve at once.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind all ingredients together.
Chill.
Each serving contains 8 calories.

title: brownie frosting
directions: Mix with electric mixer.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and boil with onion powder and salt.
Meanwhile, mix mayonnaise and pickle relish in a large bowl.
Cut up and add boiled eggs.
Cut up cooked potatoes while hot and add to mayonnaise mixture.
When cool, add more mayonnaise and more pickle, if necessary.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix ingredients (except grapes) until smooth.
Gently stir in grapes.
May top with Bits of Brickle.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice flank steak across the grain into thin strips.
Brown steak.
Add onions, pepper, tomatoes, bean sprouts, garlic salt, ginger and water.
Cook until tender, then add the cornstarch. Mix with a little bit of water for thickening.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: holiday cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Mash contents of can of cranberries and add to jello.
Pour into mold and place in refrigerator until it sets.
Very good.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soups and sour cream.
Place in a casserole dish. Stir oleo with crumbled crackers and poppy seed and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut creams
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until well combined.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Chill about 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch rounds or ovals.

title: pepper marmalade steaks
directions: Rub pepper into both sides of steaks.
Place on broiler pan, keeping steaks 2 to 3 inches away from broiler element.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Add cottage cheese, sour cream, chives and dill.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: steak diane
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a pan.
Add green onions.
Saute for a few minutes.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, parsley and lemon juice.
Heat through.
Melt and heat remaining butter in another skillet.
Add steaks to pan.
Saute quickly about 2 minutes per side.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spoon the butter-onion mixture over steaks in pan.
Sprinkle with green onion and serve.

title: finger paint
directions: Moisten cornstarch with enough cold water to make a smooth paste.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Cook mixture until clear and smooth.
Stir mixture continuously while cooking.
Add soap flakes and beat.
Add glycerine for glossiness and food coloring for color.
Store in a covered jar.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Soak dates and nuts in water until softened.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread into cooled baked pie shells.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Lemonade may be substituted for limeade to make lemon pies.

title: coke cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar and flour.
In a saucepan, place margarine, oil, cocoa and Coke.
Bring to a boil; do not boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add eggs, soda, vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Fold in small marshmallows.
Pour ingredients into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Place jellied cranberry sauce in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth. Add cranberry apple drink concentrate, partially thawed lemonade concentrate and spices. Mix on low speed until well blended and smooth. Pour mixture into a large freezer-safe, non-metallic container. Add water to mixture; stir well. Cover and freeze 2 hours. Remove from freezer; stir. Cover and continue freezing for 8 hours or overnight.

title: fruit nut cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour and salt.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and fruit. Chill 1 hour.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry lime bread
directions: Zest is grated lime rind.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Separate eggs and add to creamed mixture, one egg yolk added at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add carrots, flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Add flour mixture slowly to creamed mixture. Then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan (large).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake batter as directed on package but substitute by using the listed ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: festive hot drink
directions: In the pot of a percolating coffee pot, pour cranberry juice and apple cider.
In the basket, put brown sugar and cinnamon sticks.
Perk until ready.

title: mexican coffee
directions: Add liquors to coffee cup; pour coffee over.
Add a dollop of cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Boil all together about 2 hours or until thick and desired consistency, stirring frequently.
Pour into hot sterile jars and seal at once or can eat right away.
It also freezes well.

title: batter for vegetables
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
This is a good batter for any vegetable.
Dip in mixture and fry.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Place bread in greased casserole.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla together. Pour over bread.
Drizzle chocolate-butter mixture on top of the bread pudding; do not stir.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8. Yummy!

title: rocky road
directions: In medium saucepan, melt chocolate over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in buttered, 8-inch square pan; chill.
Cut into squares.
Yields about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: fruit pie
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Spread dough out on pan.
(A rolling pin over wax paper works well.)
Cook the cookie dough according to package directions.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Spread the mixture on the cooled cookie crust.
Add assorted fruits to the top in colorful sections.
Kiwi, strawberries, pineapple, etc. work well.

title: green bean almondine
directions: Combine all.
Boil 5 minutes.
Turn heat to low.
Continue to cook for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with crushed pineapple; add marshmallows, pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and then cook broccoli. Add other ingredients in a 2 quarts casserole dish. Bake at 350 degree for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "a" wing's favorite blueberry muffins
directions: Grease a 12 cup muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.
Crush 1/2 cup berries and add to batter.
Fold remaining berries into batter and spoon into muffin pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 20 minutes or until tests done.
Cool 5 minutes and turn out onto wire rack.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Pour butter over pecans, stirring to coat well.
Arrange pecans in a single layer on a baking sheet; sprinkle with salt. Bake at 275° for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, frosting mix and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 60 minutes.
Do not test with toothpick!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful; press with a fork to flatten.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar or colored sugar.
Bake 10 minutes, but not browned.

title: snow pudding
directions: Chill evaporated milk.
Mix hot water with jello.
Whip after partially jelled.
Mix lemon juice and sugar with whipped jello. Fold whipped milk into gelatin.

title: punch
directions: Freeze cranberries in cranberry juice in plastic container or mold.
Unmold approximately 1/2 hour to 1 hour before serving punch and place in large punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Makes 36 punch-cup servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes, covered at 350°.

title: baked spinach and cheese
directions: Blend spinach, flour, salt and pepper. Stir in remaining ingredients. Turn into buttered casserole. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until set. Serves 6-8.

title: apple salad
directions: Boil 3 minutes together the pineapple, juice and 2/3 cup sugar. After 3 minutes, into mixture mix lemon Jell-O and cream cheese. Beat. Cool to lukewarm. Add apple, pecans and celery. Can be fixed in a flat dish (square) or in round bowl to spoon when served. Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: stuffed bacon rolls
directions: Combine bread crumbs, apple, onion, parsley, salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add egg and milk; mix well.
Shape crumb mixture into balls, using about 1 rounded tablespoonful for each ball. Cut each slice of bacon in half crosswise.
Wrap half of a bacon slice around each ball.
Secure with a metal pick or wooden toothpick.
Place on a wire rack set in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 or 35 minutes, or until bacon is brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 20 to 22 appetizers.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, mushroom, garlic, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Cook until meat is done; drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Stir well.
Simmer and cover for 10-15 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Pour soup over chicken. Add 1/2 can of water.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, celery salt and pepper.
Place bacon slices over top of chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally with pan juices.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes its own great gravy!

title: egg rolls with a twist
directions: Chop cabbage fine, steam until soft.
Drain well until cool. Meantime in non-stick skillet have cooking oil hot.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon 2-3 tablespoons of filling on each wrap.
Roll up as you would egg roll.
Wet edge a little to seal it together.
Fry until desired darkness.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; add soup and pimento.
Mix well.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake in a moderate oven until it bubbles.
Add onion rings and brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix hamburger, bell pepper, onion and crumbled crackers together.
Bake at 350°
until it begins to crack.
Take out of oven and spread ketchup on top and place in oven until brown.
Serve.

title: blender breakfast
directions: Combine banana, milk, honey and bran in blender or food processor.
Whirl until smooth.
Pour into tall glass.

title: dried lima bean casserole
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Next day, add pinch of baking soda; bring to boil.
Skim off foam.
Lower heat; cover partially and cook over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, until beans are tender.
Preheat oven to 250°.
(Cooking time will vary; you do not want mushy beans.) Drain and transfer beans to oiled 2-quart flat baking dish.
In same kettle, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and molasses; cook over low heat for about 2 minutes, until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; let cool slightly. Stir in sour cream, onion, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour the butter-sugar sauce over the beans; mix lightly.
Arrange bacon pieces on top.
Cover and bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, removing the cover after 30 minutes.
Garnish with fresh chopped parsley.

title: outdoor lemony barbecue chicken
directions: In a saucepan, mix together catsup, lemonade, water, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, corn oil, onion and flavor enhancer.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.

Place chicken over hot coals on grill, skin side up, about 8 inches from heat. Cook, basting frequently and turning several times, about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix well
with hands, then press mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then let cool.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Let cheese stand and soften.
Cream it and stir in pineapple. When smooth, add 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onions and seasoned salt.
Chill well.
Form into ball and roll in remaining pecans. (Mix 1 to 2 tablespoons parsley flakes with pecans prior to rolling.)
Chill.
Garnish with twists of pineapple, cherries and parsley.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli, discarding leaves and toughest part of stem. Blanch entire head in boiling water for 1 minute.
Rinse under cold water.
Break off florets and cut remaining stems (peeled if desired) into 2 inch pieces.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Spread broccoli pieces in one layer on a greased baking sheet.
Roast at 450° for 5 minutes, turn broccoli pieces over and continue roasting until broccoli begins to brown, about 5 minutes more.
Whisk together soy sauce, vinegar and oils.
Stir in 3 tablespoons sesame seed.
When broccoli is done, transfer to a bowl and pour dressing over it, stirring gently to coat.
Sprinkle with remaining tablespoon sesame seed.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Yield: 8 servings.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 2 g, fat 9 g, calories 94.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well until blended.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375° and bake 40 to 45 minutes longer until crust is golden and custard is set.

title: overnight french toast(good for a brunch)
directions: Pancake batter must be soft so that it can spread in a thin layer over the base of a hot frying pan.
Mix the batter until smooth and leave for 30 minutes or longer in a cool place before using. Do not stir again.
Use a pan with a heavy base.
Heat and spread with oil.
Pour off excess oil. The pan must be very hot when the batter is poured in.
Use a measuring cup or a soup ladle and use the same amount of batter for each pancake. Allow batter to spread quickly to cover the pan.
Keep pancakes hot by layering on top of each other in a dish and keep the dish warm over boiling water. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar just before serving.
Ovens tend to make pancakes tough.

title: andrea's scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter until coarse.
Add milk; mix until dough forms.
Pat dough into 1/2-inch thick circles (handle as little as possible).
Place on greased and floured baking sheet.
Score in 8 to 12 slices.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Adjust oven temperature to 350° and continue baking another 5 to 10 minutes; nice during the holidays.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 1/2 of sugar.
Layer as crust on bottom of pan.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar.
Layer on pretzel crust.
Drain pineapple; cook juice, remaining sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add pineapple; pour over top.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix these ingredients well.
Use for all kinds of fresh fruit.

title: nut refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift salt and soda in with flour.
Add broken nuts last.
Roll into 3 or 4 long rolls and wrap in waxed paper.
The dough will be soft, but put it into waxed paper and shape it.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: gram's cole slaw
directions: Fill cup rest of the way with vinegar and add a little water. Fry bacon.
Drain almost all of grease off and add sugar mixture. Mix together and warm just a little.
Mix with a head of very thinly shredded cabbage.

title: vegetable fromage
directions: In large skillet, stir-fry carrots, zucchini, peppers and garlic in margarine until crisp-tender.
Reduce heat to low.
Add process cheese spread, half and half and basil; stir until process cheese spread is melted.
Add pasta; mix lightly.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: easy steak crock-pot
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in quarters. Place on bottom of pot. Cut meat in medium-size pieces. Place on top of potatoes. Add onion soup mix. Pour mushroom soup over the top and add water. Cover and cook on low for 6 hours. Makes great gravy.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak in 1/8-inch strips.
Brown in oil with onion and garlic.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add green pepper and bouillon; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix cornstarch, soy sauce and water. Add to meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: healthy walnut bread
directions: Mix 2 3/4 cups all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, walnuts, wheat germ, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat water, yogurt and butter until hot to touch (125° to 130°).
Stir into dry mixture.
Mix only enough remaining flour to make stiff dough.
On lightly floured surface, knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half to 12 x 18-inch rectangle.
Roll up short end and pinch seam and ends.
Place in 2 greased 8 3/4 x 4 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.

title: kesakeitto(summer soup)
directions: In a large kettle, bring water and the potatoes to a boil.
Add the carrots and bring to a boil.
Cook a few minutes.
Add the peas, beans and cauliflower and cook until nearly tender.
Pour into a colander.
Save the broth and vegetables.
Mix the egg yolk, melted butter and flour to a paste.
Add to the milk and stir. Return the broth to the kettle and add the flour mixture slowly, as the broth heats, to thicken the broth.
(If it doesn't thicken enough, prepare and add more of the egg, butter and flour mixture.) Return the vegetables to the broth and heat gently.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Before serving, sprinkle with chopped parsley or dill.

title: salmon pat
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in food processor fitted with steel blade.
Add last two ingredients and pulse briefly.
Spoon into serving bowl and chill for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add blueberries.
Make a well and add remaining ingredients all at once.
Stir only enough to dampen flour.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 25-30 minutes.
Makes 12 large of 18 smaller muffins.

title: peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease a long pan.
On low heat, stir together first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cereal and press into pan.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Makes 32.

title: pork chops on rice
directions: Brown pork chops in a skillet, then remove from skillet.
Add water to skillet; bring to a boil and pour over rice that has been spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Lay pork chops on top of rice. Add consomme.
Top with onions and bell pepper.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken elegant
directions: Simmer chicken in water until done. Remove meat from bones. Reserve broth. Chop chicken into bite size pieces.
Toss chicken with sour cream and soup; turn into casserole dish.
Melt butter in 1 cup of chicken broth.
Pour broth mixture over stuffing cubes.
Sprinkle cubes with poultry seasoning and mix until cubes are coated. Pour cubes over chicken and sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain pineapple well and reserve 3 tablespoons juice. Combine juice, sugar and flour. Add cheese and pineapple. In small bowl, combine melted butter and crushed Ritz crackers. Grease 9 x 13 pan. Pour in pineapple mixture and top with Ritz mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, or until golden.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Place hamburger and onion in a large kettle; brown meat. Drain fat.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, cabbage and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Sprinkle rice into mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Melt margarine; stir in cinnamon and sugar. Spoon in the middle of flattened biscuit; fold biscuit over. Spoon a little of the margarine, cinnamon and sugar mixture on top. Bake per biscuit instructions.

title: flavored rice mixes(healthy mixes u-make)
directions: Combine all the ingredients together and store in a zip lock plastic bag or sealable container. This will keep up to 4 months if stored in a cool, dark and dry place. With brown rice, you may want to keep it in the freezer.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients except sour cream.
Pour half mixture in pan and refrigerate until firm. Pour sour cream over this.
Then add the remaining half of mixture.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Grease casserole dish and line with corn tortillas. Layer in order hamburger meat, beans, cheese, more corn tortillas, soup, tomatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken parm-zip
directions: Heat electric broiling (not necessary to preheat gas broiler). Stir together salad dressing, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Place chicken on rack of broiler pan.
Brush with half of sauce.
Broil 5 to 7 inches from heat, 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining sauce.
Continue broiling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ruby apple salad
directions: In a bowl stir gelatin and candies in boiling water until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
fold in apples, celery and pecans.
Pour into a 1 qt. serving bowl.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine beaten eggs, milk and salt.
Add sugar, flour and coconut and bake until set, about 20 minutes, at 300°.

title: spice pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, saving syrup.
Blend all ingredients, except pineapple.
Bring to rolling boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple and bring to a boil again for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Pour into serving dish and refrigerate.

title: pralines
directions: Mix together.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir until mixture begins to coat pecans.
Drop on foil or drop on wax paper which has been placed over newspaper.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Combine all three ingredients in a heavy saucepan until cheese is completely melted and mixture is bubbly.
Serve hot with cubed Italian bread, vegetables, crackers, etc.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad(everyone likes my chicken salad!)
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together and spread on sandwich bread.
Can also be served on lettuce leaf, or as a dip with crackers.
Serves 4.

title: chicken rice casserole 1
directions: Combine rice, chicken, soup and milk in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease casserole dish and transfer mixture to dish. On stove, melt butter; add crackers, making sure to coat all of the crumbs.
Remove from heat and cover rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until center is hot.
Do not cover while baking, crackers will not get crispy.
For an added touch, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Place instant pudding mix in large bowl.
Add milk and stir until pudding is dissolved.
Stir in Cool Whip and sour cream. Slice bananas into mixture.
Then in another large bowl, alternate vanilla wafers with pudding mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend soup mix, sour cream, mayo and lemon juice.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts; chill.
Serve with bread cubes in hollowed out loaf of bread or with raw vegetables.

title: lighter chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil and garlic.
Brown chicken 5 minutes each side. Remove chicken and set aside.
Cook onion and green or red pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, including chicken. Cover and simmer about 1/2 hour.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice or linguine.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Put olives in food processor to chop.
Add cream cheese and dressing.
Mix all together.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Stir together egg and flour in saucepan.
Add juice mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool.
When mixture is cool, add pineapple chunks and cheese.
Can add miniature marshmallows and pecans, if desired.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk and water.
Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot dogs
directions: Boil hot dogs first with hot sauce.
Boil noodles.
Hard boil egg.
Cut the hot dogs into big chunks.
Cut 2 big chunks of cheese.
Mix together with noodles.
Add pineapple, chopped up. Add pizza sauce.
Put in a pan and bake in the oven until bubblely.

title: neiman-marcus cookie recipe
directions: Cream butter and both sugars well, add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Mix in flour, blended oatmeal, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bars and pecans. Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes (do not overbake cookies).

title: round steak stroganoff
directions: Cut steak across the grain into thin strips (1/2 x 2-inches). Sprinkle with meat tenderizer according to package directions; let meat stand.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet over medium-high heat.
Add steak; brown gently.
Remove steak from the skillet.
Melt remaining butter in skillet; stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Stir in bouillon, red wine and onion.
Drain mushrooms; add mushroom liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Return meat to sauce; add mushrooms.
Cover, lower heat and simmer for about 30 minutes, or until meat is tender. Stir in sour cream; heat, but do not boil.
Serve with hot noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: picante sauce(the kind put in ruth's pot of chili.)
directions: Blend and boil for 30 minutes.
Place in sterile jars and water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 pints of sauce.
This recipe can be halved, doubled or tripled.
If you use 32 cups of tomatoes, the yield is about 12 quarts.

title: finger jello
directions: For each treat, you'll need 1 pretzel twist, 2 pretzel sticks, melted white chocolate and 3 candy-coated chocolate candies (2 green and 1 red).

title: pineapple-sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in large saucepan.
Stir in pineapple (juice and all), sour cream and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat and stir often until thickened and it comes to a boil, then cook and stir constantly for about 5 minutes.
Slowly add beaten egg yolks and continue to cook for 2 minutes longer.
Cool. Spoon into large baked pie shell.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into Pyrex dish or muffin tins which have been sprayed with cooking spray.
Cook 40 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine and set aside.

title: toffee delight
directions: Lay graham crackers closely together in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Mix whipped whipping cream and can of Hershey's syrup together. Take 1/3 of this whipped cream mixture and spread over the crackers. Put on another layer of graham crackers, 1/3 whipped cream and then 1/3 layer of each, ending with whipped cream on top. Crush 3 pieces of Heath bars and sprinkle on top of dessert. Chill 24 hours covered.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray tins with Pam.
Combine first five ingredients.
Set aside.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Add hot water last.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Marinate peas in dressing until thawed.
Cook tortellini; drain, rinse and cool.
Add marinated peas.
Add other ingredients.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.

title: pecan dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with flour and pecans.
Put in bottom of dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of flour and pecans.
Mix instant pudding and milk with mixer together and pour on top of other ingredients.
Spread rest of Cool Whip over this and crushed pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese buds
directions: Combine cheese and butter; mix until well blended.
Sift flour and pepper.
Gradually stir into cheese mixture.
Roll 1/4 inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into 1-inch rounds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; brush with egg white.
Top with pecan half.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Lightly saute onion and butter.
Mix all ingredients together, except tomatoes.
Hollow out tomatoes, salt the inside of tomatoes and let drain upside down for about 1/2 hour.
Place the spinach mixture inside tomatoes and mound on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Mixture can be made ahead.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix until blended. Stir in crab meat, cheese and onions.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole deluxe
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine tuna, cooked macaroni, sour cream, mushrooms, olives and cashews.
Add enough milk to thin mixture to taste; mix well.
Transfer tuna mixture to a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna party sandwiches
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add mayonnaise until smooth to spread.
Spread on whole wheat bread; trim edges and cut in quarters.

title: hopping john
directions: Pan-fry bacon and onion in heavy saucepan until onion
is tender but not brown. Stir in rice, water, salt, hot pepper sauce and beans. Bring to a boil, cover and cook over low heat for about 15 minutes or until done. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix both cans pineapple and the juice.
Sprinkle pudding mix on top.
Let mixture sit for 3 minutes.
Carefully mix in nuts and coconut.
Blend together.
Fold in whipped topping and marshmallows.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, salt, meal and vinegar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add margarine, which has been melted, and vanilla. Blend until thick and creamy.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and cook at 375° for about 40 minutes or until crust and filling are a deep golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together over hot water.
Beat eggs and mix sugar into them.
Add chocolate mixture, flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: butter balls or cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts in a large bowl.
Mix well. After mixed into a dough-like texture, add the nuts; blend well into dough. Chill at least 3 hours in refrigerator.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Form dough into balls or any shape. Bake 25 to 30 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prepare a sheet of aluminum foil and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Bake cookies until golden brown on bottom.
Place cookies on powdered sugar and sprinkle immediately on top with sugar. Cool about 1/2 hour.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Crush tortilla chips.
Spread half on bottom of pan.
Brown turkey and onion.
Add tomato sauce.
Pour on top of chips.
Mix sour cream, cottage cheese, olives and chilies.
Pour on top of turkey mixture.
Top with Jack and Cheddar cheese.
Spread remaining chips on top.
Serves 12.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in a large nonmetal bowl and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sourdough starter, 1/4 cup sugar, oil, salt, eggs and 3 cups flour.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 minutes.
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place free from draft (put in sink with warm water) 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in size.
Punch down and divide into 2 loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Brush with oil.
Let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in quart jars with 2 garlic buds, 1 hot pepper, dill and 1 teaspoon alum.
Heat water, vinegar and salt; pour over cucumbers and seal.
Let set about 3 weeks before opening.

title: surprise peanut butter pie
directions: Add enough powdered sugar to peanut butter to make it crumbly; set aside.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook on medium heat while stirring with whisk.
Cook until very thick.
In the bottom of baked pie shell, add the peanut butter (save enough for top of pie and meringue).
Pour in filling and sprinkle more peanut butter mixture.
Pour beaten meringue on pie and sprinkle with peanut butter mixture.
Brown in 400° oven.

title: double peanut pie
directions: Prepare pastry for one peanut pie.
Use to line one 9-inch pie plate and make decorative edge.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: company's coming chicken casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Put uncooked rice on bottom of baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl and stir well. Reserve enough to spread over chicken.
Pour remainder over rice. Place on chicken; cover with remaining soup mix.
Cook covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove lid the last 15 minutes of cooking time to brown meat.
Recipe and cooking time may easily be doubled.

title: kourabiethes(greece)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolk, dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well and shape in balls (small).
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll them in powdered sugar.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and one can tomato sauce.
Soak cabbage leaves in boiling water 4 minutes.
Drain.
Place equal amounts meat on each leaf.
Roll up; fold end over and fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in hot Wesson oil in heavy skillet.
Mix the remaining can of tomato sauce and the brown sugar and lemon juice. Pour over rolls and simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: mexican or calico beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, fry bacon crisp; remove to drain.
Brown ground beef.
Drain.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift into creamed butter mixture.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs and walnuts; mix again.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: yodels ice cream cake
directions: You will need a Bundt pan.

title: 30-minute meat balls
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion, peppers and seasonings.
Mix in half of the tomato sauce (reserve remainder).
Form meat mixture into meat balls.
Top with reserved tomato sauce.
Meat balls are baked in rectangle baking pan.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese and olive slices (optional).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 4 or more.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Form into walnut-size balls.
Dip top half of ball into water; then into sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cook corn in butter.
Add salt.
When corn is done, add remaining ingredients and stir.
Bake 1 hour in greased casserole at 300°.

title: hot buttered rum sauce
directions: In medium sauce pan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, cream, butter and salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens. Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in rum extract and pecans. Serve warm over ice cream. Makes 2 cups.

title: thanksgiving applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to cream mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add nuts, raisins and orange slices.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven in a greased, paper-lined tube pan.

title: squash corn bread
directions: Mix squash, milk, eggs, salt, cheese and muffin mix, then stir in melted margarine and mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch pan, greased well, and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
During last 5 minutes, sprinkle cheese on top and finish baking.
Very good.

title: chess pie(for 2 pies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add vanilla, vinegar and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Start cooking at 300°.
Raise heat in 10 minutes to 350°.
Bake about 50 to 55 minutes or until pie is firm.

title: windy's shake
directions: In blender mix all the ingredients.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add flour, salt and baking soda together and mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press mixture into a greased pan.
Top with raspberry preserves and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Drop balls into greased mini tart tins.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Press small Reese's peanut butter cup into center.
Let cool and dump out.
Makes 24 to 30.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken until almost done, remove from bone and set aside. Mix soups together with 1 can water.
Slice celery, green peppers and hot peppers.
Slice onions very thin.
Put mixture of chicken and soup on bottom of large covered roasting pan.
Then put a layer of tortillas; add chicken, peppers, onions and celery, then cheese. Do each layer alternately until all ingredients are used.
Top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for about an hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: fruit juice cake(diabetic)
directions: Combine prunes and orange peel; set aside.
Cream dry milk with margarine.
Add egg and orange juice; mix well.
In another bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Add salt.
Add to prune mix; stir well.
Then stir in dry ingredients.
Put in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
One slice contains 101 calories.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour green beans into casserole dish after draining into separate bowl.
Add most of the French onions, onion powder, salt and pepper.

title: seasoned green beans
directions: Quickly stir-fry 1 pound of beans in oil in large skillet over high heat.
Remove beans and set aside.
Stir-fry remaining beans and then add reserved beans.
Reduce heat.
Stir in water and salad dressing mix.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until beans are crisp-tender.
Makes 6 cups or 10 to 12 servings.
(Well received at potlucks and with family.)

title: hamburger pie
directions: Pepper and brown ground sausage, ground chuck and onion until done.
Add cream of mushroom soup, mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with the other pie shell and crimp the edges to seal.
Cook on 350° until brown.
Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; let cool.
Cut up.
Save 1 cup broth.
Mix soup, milk and margarine; beat until thick.
Add chicken and mix well.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Place strawberries in medium bowl; sprinkle lightly with 1/4 cup sugar.
Let stand until thawed, then slice.
Combine flour, 2 cups sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in large bowl; mix well.
Stir oil and eggs into strawberries; add strawberry mixture to flour mixture; add pecans and blend until dry ingredients are just moistened (do not overmix).
Divide batter between two 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool bread in pans for 10 minutes, then turn loaves out and cool completely.
Sprinkle tops of loaves with sugar.

title: praline cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan (sprayed with Pam); will be thick. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Place the turkey in a greased casserole.
Spread with the soup.
Top with the two cups of stuffing.
Bake in 325° preheated oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add two cheeses and soup and melt together.
Stir in cooked and drained broccoli.
Add almonds.
Serve hot with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2-quarts.

title: rose boyle's lemon goddess pie
directions: Make and bake your own favorite pie crust.

title: tangy cole slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sandwich spread, mustard and parsley.
Mix well; set aside.
Toss cabbage with relish, celery and onion.
Add enough mayonnaise mixture to moisten all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease pizza pan.
Separate rolls and place on pizza pan; spread to form crust.
Sprinkle browned sausage evenly.
Sprinkle with hash browns and Cheddar cheese. Pour egg mixture over top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
"Can be made and refrigerated the night before."

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together, except crescent rolls.
Shape in loaf (7 x 3-inches).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Batter will be thin. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350 for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: wine pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with electric beater 5 minutes. Pour into greased round tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken with caper-lemon sauce for two
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
In a 9-inch non-stick skillet, heat oil; add chicken and quickly brown, turning once (about 3 minutes each side).
Remove and keep warm.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix together and pour into a muffin tin. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until browned.

title: ham glaze and sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir corn syrup, sugar, mustard and ginger.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes. Brush 1/2 cup on ham during last hour of baking.

title: minister's dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and spread fruit filling over bottom. Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Pour melted margarine over and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease or spray loaf pan. Mix sugar and margarine together. Stir in eggs until blended. Add bananas and water and blend for 30 seconds. Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts until moistened. Stir in nuts. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife or pick comes out clean.

title: classic french silk pie
directions: Bake pie shell; cool.
Beat sugar and butter in a 1 1/2-quart bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in chocolate, coffee, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until set, 3 to 4 hours, or cover with plastic wrap and freeze at least 8 hours.
If pie is frozen, remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: beef and vegetable stew
directions: Brown stew on all four sides.
Add small amount of water.
Let beef simmer until vegetables are prepared.
Cut carrots crosswise into 3/8-inch thick slices.
Add to stew beef.
Cut celery across stalk into slices.
Cut onions into 1-inch dices and potatoes into 3/4-inch dices.
Add celery, onions, potatoes, tomatoes and juice to stew.
Allow to cook for one hour.
Then add peas and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for an additional 15 minutes.
Then serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and cocoa.
Pour into milk.
Stir together until dissolved.
Add margarine and egg yolks.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked 9-inch crust and top with meringue made from egg whites.
Brown in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Grease crock-pot with 2 teaspoons oil.
Put all ingredients (except cheese) in crock-pot and gently mix.
Layer the two kinds of cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.
Do not open or stir during cooking.
(I usually cook it 3 hours and 15 minutes.)

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar when done.

title: plain muffins
directions: Measure and sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg; add milk and add melted shortening.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in microwave 10 minutes on High.
Stir about half way through.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed avocado salad
directions: Cut avocado in half and remove seed.
Fill center with combination of cottage-chive cheese and cream cheese.
Put halves back together.
Chill thoroughly.
At serving time, remove skin and slice avocado crosswise into rings.
Serve on crisp salad greens.

title: chili with chicken
directions: Cook in crock pot; freezes well.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Dice celery.
Boil until tender; drain.
Dice onion; saute in oleo.
Add flour to oleo/onion mixture; stir until smooth.
Add milk and chicken granules.
Boil until thick.
Beat with mixer or wire whisk until smooth.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Drain shrimp; add to soup and milk mixture.
Heat slowly to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
While cooking, add 1/2 stick butter.
Remove from heat; cool. Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Line bottom of casserole with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Pour pudding mixture over vanilla wafers.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar to taste.
Pour on top of pudding.
Brown and serve.
This recipe may also be used for chocolate pie.
Add 3 tablespoons cocoa.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cut up Velveeta into a crock-pot.
Add other ingredients. When it all melts together, it's done.
Serve as a dip with Tostitos or other type of corn chips.

title: pork chop noodle casserole
directions: Brown chops in fat until golden brown.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt. Combine remaining salt, onion, Worcestershire sauce, tomato soup and water.
Place noodles in a casserole; add tomato soup mixture.
Arrange chops overlapping around inner edge.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fat-free salad dressing
directions: Combine in a jar. Cover tightly and shake vigorously. Chill.

title: mild chili
directions: Brown beef on stove top.
Drain and set aside.
Drain kidney beans.
Combine kidney beans, pork and beans, tomatoes, onion mix and ketchup in casserole dish.
Mix together then add beef and mix again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: domino sugar pound cake
directions: Sift sugar, salt and
mace in large mixing bowl.
Cream sugar mixture and
butter
until	fluffy.
Add
extract.	Beat eggs into mixture, one at
a	time.
Add flour and milk alternately to mixture.
Beat well.
Bake	in
10-inch
tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15
minutes.
Allow
cake to cool in pan 5 minutes; turn out on rack.

title: australian meat pie
directions: Brown onion and beef in heavy saucepan.
Add brown gravy, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook mixture fully about 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and skim off fat.
Fill deep dish pie shell and place regular one on top.
Crimp and pierce top with fork.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: cheesie potatoes
directions: Cook and grate potatoes.
Then, in saucepan on low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Stir occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes.

title: blueberry-yogurt muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix orange juice and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Divide batter evenly among 12 muffin cups coated with Pam vegetable cooking spray.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar evenly over muffins. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan immediately.
There are 150 calories per muffin.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Combine refried beans and taco seasoning; spread in 8-inch square pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small casserole dish; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine graham crumbs, pecans, sugar and margarine in mixing bowl. Reserve 1/3 cup. Press remaining mixture in a 13 x 9 baking pan. Bake 6 minutes. Remove and let cool.

title: five-flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each one.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add flour.
Make dough stiff. Knead on lightly floured place.
Put in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and grate sweet potatoes, about 9 cups.
Combine all ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir and bake, covered, 30 minutes more.

title: uncooked fruitcake
directions: Mix all fruits and nuts in large pan (I use dishpan).
Crush vanilla wafers with rolling pin.
Add wafers and milk to nuts and fruit.
Roll in 4 rolls.
Roll in aluminum foil and refrigerate. Will keep in refrigerator 3 weeks.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into ready made pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheddar-beer cocktail spread
directions: Combine in a medium bowl and mix until very smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
A quantity can be stored by filling crock and sealing top with paraffin.
Will keep refrigerated for several weeks. Remove from refrigerator 1/2 hour before serving.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Combine butter and sugar until mixed.
Add eggs, vanilla and bananas, beating with wire whisk. Add salt, baking soda, baking powder and finally flour.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in buttermilk, then walnuts, if desired.
Bake at 375° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes approximately 2 to 3 loaves.

title: cheese shrimp dip
directions: Thaw and drain shrimp.
Chop into small pieces.
Place first 4 ingredients in food grinder.
Add pepper sauce and shrimp.
This can be refrigerated for weeks.

title: murphy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter, and cocoa in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Stir slightly.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, oatmeal and nuts to the mixture.
Drop by 1/2 tablespoon on wax paper.
Cool.

title: baklava
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 15 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
In a large bowl combine walnuts, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cinnamon.
Lay 1 sheet phyllo in pan; brush with butter.
Repeat until 1/2 of phyllo is used.
Sprinkle with walnut mixture. Repeat phyllo layers with butter.
Using a sharp knife, cut halfway through layers of phyllo.
Bake in oven 1 1/4 hours or until deep golden brown.
Meanwhile, in a medium-size saucepan, heat water and 1 1/2 cups sugar over medium heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Spoon over Baklava.
Let stand 4 hours before cutting.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Mix cornstarch with 2 teaspoons water.
Add a little of the hot tomato mixture in with the cornstarch and blend.
Slowly pour the cornstarch mixture into the sauce, stirring well to blend.
Add shrimp and bell pepper.
Cover and simmer until shrimp are done, about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: one minute icing
directions: Mix together and bring to a full boil.
Continue boiling for 1 minute.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix wafer crumbs and butter; press into 9-inch pie pan to form shell.
Combine marshmallows and milk in heavy skillet, stirring constantly over low heat until marshmallows melt.
Let cool.
Add liqueurs; fold mixture into whipped cream.
Put into pie shell. Sprinkle grated semi-sweet chocolate over top.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball. Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan at once.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: chicken and fruit salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together yogurt, mayonnaise dressing or salad dressing, ginger and lemon peel. Add melon, chicken, grapes and celery; toss until mixed. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or up to 4 hours. Serve on 6 lettuce and/or kale-lined plates. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken cheese enchiladas
directions: Spray tortillas with Pam, heat in microwave until soft (approximately 1 minute).
Mix chicken, 1 cup cheese and sour cream.
Place chicken mixture in tortillas and roll.
Place in 9x13 inch pan.
Sprinkle with 2 cups cheese.
Mix soup, chilies and water.
Pour over.
Bake at 350 degrees until heated through. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, green pepper, garlic and salt in a large bowl.
Add ice water to cover.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well.
Combine 1 cup water, sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, turmeric and mustard in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil.
Add zucchini mixture and boil 10 minutes.

title: granny smith apple blossom cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at low speed.
Fold in diced apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool cake on pan rack.

title: corn pie
directions: In unbaked pie shell, layer potatoes, corn and hard-boiled eggs.
Sprinkle parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Put small pats of butter on top.
Put milk in until shows through the corn. Cover top with unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: peas in wine sauce
directions: Saut mushrooms and onions in butter.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, dried marjoram and sherry.	This may be stored in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream butter and honey until fluffy.
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Mix in nuts.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Let cool 10 minutes and roll in powdered sugar.

title: butterscotch haystacks candy
directions: Melt chips in microwave.
When melted, stir in other ingredients.
Spoon (quickly) onto wax paper.
You can substitute chocolate chips and/or coconut.

title: unbelivable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the four ingredients together with a spoon. The mixture will be sticky. Be sure it is mixed well. Roll into small balls and place one ungreased cookie sheet and press slightly with fork to flatten. Place about 1 inch apart. Cook 15 to 20 minutes in a 350 degree oven, or until cookies are light brown and soft when removed form oven. Thats right no flour or baking powder.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices.
Stir in creamed mixture, then stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Form into small balls; place about 1 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: toni's easy biscuits
directions: Mix and roll out on floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix all together.
