Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes in a pan with sides.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Chop, slice, etc. the red cabbage.
Bring ingredients to boil; turn down heat and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Taste; if more vinegar or sugar is needed, use to your taste.
After cabbage has cooled, place in pint and quart containers and freeze.
Excellent.
Keeps for months and up to a year in freezer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, egg, sugar and brown sugar together.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and press with a fork dipped in powdered sugar to flatten.
Bake 10-12 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: vegetarian cottage cheese loaf
directions: Saute onions, celery, bell peppers and carrots in small amount of oil.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly, folding in oil and eggs last.

title: cheeseball
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Cover and place in refrigerator until it gets hard enough to roll into ball.
May roll in pecans if desired.
Keep in refrigerator until used. Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup until warm.
Cube cream cheese and melt in soup. Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup water and add to soup.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well and pour in mold. Chill in refrigerator for at least 4 to 6 hours.

title: regular dressing
directions: Mix cornbread with milk, eggs, and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Melt butter, onions, and celery, cook until done. When cornbread is done, crumble and add all of above ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken with cream sauce
directions: In an oblong roasting pan, melt butter.
Dip both sides of chicken in butter and seasonings.
Roast at 400° for 1/2 hour each side of chicken.
After chicken is cooked on each side, add soup and milk.
Roast 30 to 45 minutes more until chicken is done. Serve with white rice.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: This recipe is pretty in a large glass bowl.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, onion and green pepper.
Add 1/4 cup salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain, but do not press, vegetables. Let set 2 to 3 hours.
Place vegetables in a large kettle. Add sugar, brown sugar, pepper, pickling spices and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Put pickling spices in a piece of cheesecloth and drop in kettle to cook.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Put into jars while hot.
Tastes good on hamburgers, hot dogs, etc.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in half around the middle.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine bread crumbs, garlic, parsley and melted butter.
Remove seeds from tomatoes, leaving as much of the tomato as possible.
Gently pat the bread crumb mixture into each half tomato and add a few drops of fresh lemon juice.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with extra parsley, if desired.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in glass baking dish or 4-inch souffle dish.
Dust top with more Parmesan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk; beat until well blended.
Add cracker crumbs; set aside until all liquid is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, to cracker crumb mixture, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese while hot.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir until it starts to boil; boil for a few minutes.
Cool and add 1 box powdered sugar and vanilla.
Use on any yellow layered cake.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Mix and add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 160 cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into ball.
Roll ball in 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: lemon cheese or curd
directions: In a large saucepan, mix lemon juice, rind and sugar.
Add butter and eggs.
Mix well; simmer slowly over a low heat, stirring steadily, until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
It will be firmer when chilled.
Pour into sterilized jars with screw top lids.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pint.
Can be doubled.

title: crunchy cheese vegetables
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, milk, chives, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Spread in a 15 in. x 10 in. x 1 in. baking pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli, following package directions.
Drain. Cook onion in salted water until tender.
Drain.
In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter, flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Blend in cream cheese until smooth.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Then spread pie filling on top of pineapple.
Next, shake dry cake mix over pie filling.
Put nuts on top of cake mix.
Dot top with margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 48 to 53 minutes.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over butter and layer butterscotch and chocolate chips over crumbs.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over chips.
Pour milk over this mixture and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares. Yield:
32 squares.

title: seasoned steak
directions: Use sirlion or any steak of your choice.
Mix a half and half mixture of lemon juice (bottled or fresh) and cooking oil and baste both sides of steak with mixture.
Sprinkle both sides of steak with lemon pepper seasoning, garlic powder and seasoned salt.
Broil or barbecue to desired doneness.

title: pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Take a rectangle shape (2 rolls) and pinch seams together.
Put pepperoni in single layer on about 3/4 of the roll.
Add cheese.
Roll as tight as possible, slice and place on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken up into bite size pieces and place in 9x13 inch baking dish.
Pour broth over chicken.
Spread soup over chicken. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix melted butter, flour and milk together.
Pour over chicken and spread evenly.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until brown.
Crust forms on top. Enjoy.

title: sloppy joes(who needs manwich when this is so easy!)
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Add vegetables and cook for 6 minutes, until vegetables are cooked.
Then add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve hot on hamburger buns. Garnish with pickle slices. (Equally as good served over hot cooked noodles, spaghetti or cooked rice.)

title: fall apple dip
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.
Chill and enjoy.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix
all
the
listed ingredients.
Refrigerate and let stand at least 2 days before baking.
Prepare muffin tins with oil or baking cups and fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°. This
batter keeps in the refrigerator for about 3 or 4 weeks.

title: orange date cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add orange peel.
Sift flour, measure and add salt and soda; sift again.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Bake in tube pan in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: eggrolls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Put into the center of eggroll wrap.
Fry until golden.
Serve with Sweet and Sour Sauce.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Brush chicken halves with sauce.
Cook slow, turning every 15 minutes to prevent burning.
Serves 5.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onion 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Add stuffing mix and oleo.
Put in baking dish and top with additional stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy spaghetti
directions: While spaghetti is cooking and meat is browning combine the sour cream, cottage cheese, 1 teaspoon of salt and green onions and let sit.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak dried apricots in water for 30 minutes.
Drain and cut into pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix with apricots. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: home freezer ice cream
directions: Add sugar and flour to eggs and mix well.
Add milk, and cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Stir constantly.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix and let cool.
Add unsweetened fruit. Pour into freezer and follow directions for your freezer.

title: dijonnaise potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. Stir in potatoes, celery and onions.
Cover and chill.
Makes 6 cups.

title: apples and rice
directions: Cook rice.
When done, add margarine, sugar, cinnamon and sliced apples.
Toss thoroughly.
Place in greased covered casserole and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or microwave 1/2 hour covered.
This is a good side dish with chicken or delicious alone.

title: dropped teacakes
directions: Cream butter in a large bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until Tea Cakes are lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: peanut butter cup brownies
directions: Cream together the peanut butter and butter. Add brown sugar, then eggs and beat.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate-peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Spread 1 pint of ice cream on bottom of pie crust.
Arrange 2/3 of chopped candies over ice cream, cover and freeze 1 hour. Spread remaining pint of ice cream over candies.
Cover and freeze 1 hour.
Decorate top of pie with whipped topping and remaining candy.
Freeze uncovered about 2 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes before cutting.
Cover and freeze remaining pie.

title: green dream(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Divide evenly into 8 dessert cups.
Chill several hours.
Each serving provides 1/2 milk, 1/2 fruit and 25 optional calories.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Cook and drain potatoes.
Mash potatoes, then add cheese and beat well. Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add 1/3 of onion mixture to potato mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Generously butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place a layer of noodles, then a layer of potato mixture.
Repeat, ending with noodles.
Pour remaining butter and onion over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage scrapple
directions: Prepare cornmeal mush according to package directions.
Fry sausage until thoroughly cooked.
Drain.
Stir in mush.
Turn into a buttered loaf pan.
Cool.
Cover and chill.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Fry slowly in a greased skillet until golden brown on each side.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots for 7 minutes in small amount of water.
Cool and drain.
Place layer of carrots, green pepper and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Beat until well blended. Pour over carrots.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Bake in 375° oven until bubbly.
Serve hot or cold.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat 1 minute and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a pie or quiche pan.
Sprinkle on the onion.
Spread the chili.
Top with cheese.
Add olives if desired. Heat through in low oven or microwave.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: old settler's beans
directions: *Or use 1 pound of each.

title: breast of chicken sandwich
directions: Spread bread with mayonnaise; layer remaining ingredients between slices.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach and cottage cheese casserole(meatless main dish)
directions: When I double this for church potlucks, I use 1/4 pound Cheddar and 1/4 pound Swiss cheese.

title: judy's quick pot roast
directions: Add roast and water to roaster.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on roast. Cover.
Set oven to 225°, cook all day.
About 1 hour before serving, add potatoes and vegetables of your choice.
Makes great gravy.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not drain pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple (do not drain pineapple) on stove until jello melts.
Remove mixture from stove; pour in serving bowl and place in refrigerator for 15 minutes until it begins to jell.
Remove and blend in buttermilk.
Place back in refrigerator until sets, about 10 minutes.
Remove and stir in Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
No fail.

title: cracker bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl and blend.
Make well in center and add remaining ingredients.
Mix dough until sticky (add warm water, if needed).
Turn onto floured board, knead dough until elastic.
Pinch off pieces (about size of golf balls). Place on large buttered pan.
Cover with damp cloth for 1 hour. (Dough may be refrigerated overnight.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, using package directions; drain.
Combine with green pepper, onion, tomatoes, cucumbers, salad dressing, Salad Supreme seasoning and salt and sugar to taste in bowl; mix well.

title: cheese sandwich casserole
directions: Arrange 6 slices bread in a greased baking dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Top with 6 bread slices.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread and cheese.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until partially divided and golden brown.
Serve with creamed vegetables.

title: ultimate cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Blend in soda.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Dough will be stiff and crumbly.
Drop dough by 1/3 cup about 4 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten to 3 1/2-inch patties. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yields 22 cookies.

title: apple strudel(apfelstrudel)
directions: Mix flour, melted butter, egg, water and salt in bowl until it forms into soft dough.
Set aside.

title: old fashion cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt, white syrup and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Cook to 232° or until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat, drop in butter and cool to lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens.
Pour into buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: mexican delight
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion and bell pepper.
Put chili, corn and beans in meat; cook 30 minutes, then pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut tamales in one-inch pieces.
Put them on top of dish. Put grated cheese on top of dish.
Put in oven to melt.
Makes a whole meal.

title: neapolitan bundt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour Bundt pan. Blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened. Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour 1/3 of batter into pan. Measure 1/2 of remaining batter into small bowl; stir in strawberry extract and food color.
Carefully pour into pan.
Stir chocolate syrup into remaining batter; pour into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: christmas ribbon mold
directions: Stir 1 cup of the boiling water into lime gelatin in medium bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in remaining 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour into 5-cup ring mold. Refrigerate 2 hours or until set but not firm.
Stir remaining 1 cup of boiling water into red flavor gelatin in medium bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in remaining 3/4 cup cold water.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until cooled.
Spoon over lime gelatin.
Gently place marshmallows in gelatin.
(Marshmallows will float to top.)
Refrigerate until firm.
Garnish as desired. Makes 10 servings.

title: apple dumplings(dessert)
directions: Boil sugar, water, butter and cinnamon for 3 minutes.
Set aside.
Roll out pie dough in large enough squares to cover apple completely.
Place cored and peeled apple on top of pie dough square.
Fill the apple with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bring sides of dough over apple and secure edges.
Place dumplings in baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Baste with syrup mixture periodically.

title: 6 english muffin split
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on muffins.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then broil for 2 minutes.

title: dried fruit spread
directions: Combine fruits and liquid in a saucepan.
Simmer until fruits are soft.
Cool.
Puree in a food processor.
Cover and store in the refrigerator.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer until done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pasta your kids will love!
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain grease off from beef.
Add tomato soup, beans and cooked macaroni.
Simmer for abut 20 to 25 minutes.
Great with Italian bread.

title: low-fat chocolate fluff
directions: In blender, combine unflavored gelatin and boiling water. Cover; blend on medium speed until gelatin dissolves.
Add dry milk and ice water.
Cover and blend until fluffy; add cocoa, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Blend until mixed.
Add ice cubes and blend on high speed until ice is crushed and mixed.
Let stand 5 minutes until set.
Spoon into dessert dishes and serve immediately or chill.
Makes 6 low-calorie servings.

title: chili sauce new mexico style
directions: Cook all ingredients, except water and flour, covered, over medium heat for 1 hour.
Blend water into flour; add to meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Yields 3 1/2 cups sauce.

title: fillet of sole parmesan
directions: Combine cheese, butter, mayo, scallions, salt and Tabasco. Set aside.
Place fish fillets, single layer, in buttered baking dish.
Brush with lemon juice and let stand 10 minutes.
Broil fillets 3 to 4 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Spread with cheese mixture and broil 2 to 3 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: beef stew
directions: Peel and cut potatoes and carrots.
Put in a large kettle; fill with water and boil.
Add garlic cloves.

title: garlic and anchovy sauce
directions: Cook the pasta in boiling salted water until al dente, "tender to the bite."
Drain and chop the anchovies into small pieces. While the pasta is cooking, heat the olive oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
Add the garlic and the anchovies.
Saute until the garlic is golden brown and the anchovies are almost melted into the sauce.
The moment the pasta is ready, drain it and place it in a large pasta bowl.
Pour the sizzling sauce over the pasta stirring well.
Add the chopped parsley if desired.
Even though there will appear to be little sauce, it will be sufficient to coat every strand of pasta.
Buon Apetito!

title: holiday brisket
directions: Brown meat on both sides in 2 tablespoons hot oil in ovenproof pan.
Remove; sprinkle with salt and pepper and set aside.
In the same pan, add vegetables and cook until wilted.
Add garlic and cook a few minutes more.
Return meat to pan.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours. Remove meat from pan.
Cool meat and sauce separately overnight. Skim fat from sauce and puree.
Slice meat and return to pan. Pour sauce over it and cook an additional 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: rose's hot peppers
directions: Soak peppers 2 to 4 hours in salt water.
Drain.
Place in jars.
Bring to boiling and add solution of oil, sugar, vinegar and garlic.
Cover and seal.
Cold pack, after water boils, 5 minutes to assure seal.

title: famous fruit salad dressing
directions: Beat cream until slightly thickened; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight to thicken.
Delicious on spinach salad, too!

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix as directed on back of box.
Add cream cheese, 1 egg and squeeze of lemon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until top splits open in center.
When cake is cooled, dump cherry pie filling on top and chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Break into small pieces.
Saute celery and onion in margarine but do not brown.
Add Cheez Whiz, both cans of soup, chicken and cooked rice.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Also use the chicken broth to cook the rice in.
Season to taste.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean soup
directions: Saute bacon until crisp. add carrots, celery, onions and cook until tender.
Add chicken stock and potatoes.

Prepare noodles and either pinch off or cut into 1 inch squares, add to stock. Add green beans and cook until potatoes and noodles are done. Take some of the liquid and mix with sour cream and put back into the soup.
Adjust seasoning and serve.
Makes 24 to 30 servings.

title: cheesy texas toast
directions: Spread butter over bread. Sprinkle with garlic powder and cheese. Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with onions or parsley if desired. Serve warm. Makes 2 servings.

title: sally's nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in greased and floured 4 x 8-inch pan.
Let rise for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Slice when cool.

title: crazy broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into small florets, then drain.
Mix together the broccoli, peanuts and raisins.
Add vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise; mix well until all ingredients are moist.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and marinate overnight.
Serve in glass bowl to accent colors.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cook on stove chocolate chips, condensed milk, butter, salt and vanilla.
Cook real low heat until melted (cool some).
Put remaining mixture on large cookie sheet.
Then put chocolate chip mixture on top of that.
Then put remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: irish freckle bread
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add mashed potatoes, butter, salt, sugar, eggs and raisins.
Mix well.
Let rise and then punch down.
Put in greased loaf pans. Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Frost with confectioners sugar and lemon juice icing.

title: easy baked beans
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels.
Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings.
To reserved drippings, add onion; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in all beans, ketchup, corn syrup, mustard and vinegar; mix well. Spoon mixture into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbling and heated through.

title: elizabeth's lasagna
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water.
Chop onion.
Brown beef, onion and garlic and drain.
Add tomatoes, paste, pepper, bay leaf and oregano.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and arrange in 3 layers: macaroni, Mozzarella, Ricotta, Parmesan and meat sauce.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and sugar together and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll into small balls.
In a double boiler, melt the paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls.
I use a toothpick to do this.
This recipe makes a lot.

title: cheap punch
directions: Heat thawed lemonade, water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add 1 gallon water, pineapple juice and food coloring in the desired color.
Serves 50.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Combine butter, flour, corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Blend beaten eggs into corn mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot 'n' spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together, bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Good with ribs, chicken, and pork.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing until well blended.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine all ingredients, except the peas and parsley, in large casserole with a tight-fitting lid.
Do not stir.
Bake for 5 to 6 hours without stirring.
Add peas and parsley to taste and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Serve the stew from the casserole.

title: frances stephens' frost-me-not-cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt chocolate and margarine in heavy pan over low heat.
Add nuts and stir until well covered.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix only until blended.
Do not beat.
Add chocolate mixture and again, mix very carefully.
Turn into paper lined baking cups.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Do not frost. Makes 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: blue cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from caps of mushrooms.
Saute stems and onions in butter; add to dry ingredients and mix.
Stuff caps with bread-cheese mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 8 minutes.
May also be broiled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Layer sliced eggs over chicken.
Mix broth with soup and Veg-All.
Pour over eggs and chicken.
Melt margarine with flour and milk; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Blend until smooth.
Pour batter in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mother's old fashioned cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add cheese slowly to make smooth mixture.
(Put through strainer if cheese is too coarse.) Add milk and vanilla; pour into baked crust.
Bake at 375° (like custard) until knife comes clean.
Sprinkle top lightly with cinnamon and serve warm or cold.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top until golden brown.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Blend cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and onions.
Cut "V" out of peppers.
Either scrape out seed or leave in.
If scraping out, a baby spoon works good.
You can dice some pieces.

title: broiled chicken
directions: Split chicken down back and place flesh-side down in foil-lined pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Fold foil over center.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Blend the first 2 ingredients, then add the rest until smooth. Good for slaw or potato salad.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, bay leaf, onion and clove.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Rub through sieve.
Combine butter and flour.
Add to tomato mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add slowly to cold milk.
Heat to boiling.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve at once. (Sieving step can be omitted.
Just remove bay leaf and clove.) Serves 4.

title: oven-baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into 2 large, shallow pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Break into smaller pieces.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix onion and potatoes together.
Sprinkle liberally with salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Dot margarine on top.
Cook in covered casserole in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Or potatoes may be sealed in foil and cooked on grill.
If done on grill, it may take longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Put all ingredients in soup pot and bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
If soup is too thick, add water as needed.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 1 cup water; stir in pie filling. Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until partially set. Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Beat cream cheese and salad dressing together; add lemon Jell-O gradually.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows. Spread over cherry layer; top with nuts and chill until firm.

title: junior mint cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, shortening, water and eggs.
Roll in 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove and push Junior Mints into center.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Peel and thinly slice carrots and onion.
Cook carrots until medium done.
Drain.
Add onions.
Combine other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Blend well and pour over carrots and onions.
Mix and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Will keep for days.
You may add 1 cup of thinly sliced green pepper and/or 1 cup thinly sliced celery.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Combine all together.
Pour over beef (roasts or steaks) and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Blend all ingredients well and serve cold.

title: swiss vegetable medley(microwave)
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Cook (microwave), covered, on High for 8 minutes; turn halfway through.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar and milk in large microwavable bowl.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add pecans.
Cover with plastic wrap, making slits in plastic wrap to allow steam to escape.
Cook in microwave for 6 minutes on High.
Stir and return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes.
It should register 234° on candy thermometer.
Beat until thick.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let it become firm before removing from paper.
Makes 24.

title: mushroom and spinach crescents
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute mushrooms and onion until tender and mushrooms are brown.
Drain juice.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and cool.
Squeeze out all moisture from spinach.
Combine spinach, mushrooms, onion and cream cheese.
Unroll crescent rolls and on large end of each triangle, place a heaping teaspoonful of the spinach mixture. Fold crescent roll over and seal completely.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven and slice in half.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
32 appetizers.

title: crab dip #1
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers or chips.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Stir carrots, raisins and vinegar well.
In separate bowl mix mayonnaise, honey and cinnamon well.
Pour over carrot mixture and stir ingredients together.
Chill two hours to two days before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk and 1/2 cup butter. Beat until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole. Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and pecans.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and baking soda into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Mix together well with a fork. Spread out evenly.
With a large spoon, make
3 holes: 1 large, 1 medium and 1 small.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Mix mustard and jelly together until jelly melts.
Then cut franks in two and put them in.
Let come to boil.
If you want to keep them warm, pour in a crock-pot or simmer on low.

title: homemade salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together tomatoes, jalapeno, green pepper, lemon juice, cilantro or parsley, garlic and pepper and onion.
Place about 1 cup of the tomato mixture and tomato sauce in a blender.
Cover and blend just until pureed.
Stir into remaining tomato mixture.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Store tightly covered in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.
Use as a dip for chips or as a topper for main dishes.
Makes about 3 1/3 cups sauce.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add 2 beaten eggs.
In blender, blend oatmeal a little at a time until it turns to powder.

title: hawaiian pineapple banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in nuts.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour wet mixture into dry mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: martha chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well and pour into a Bundt pan and cook at 350° about 35 minutes.
While cake is cooking, mix oleo, sugar, milk and chocolate chips.
Bring to a boil and boil and stir for 4 minutes.
Set aside.
As soon as cake is out of oven, poke (with a fork) holes in the top.
Pour part of the mixture into the hole, let set for a minute or two, then turn upside down on a plate.
Add pecans to the remaining filling and spread over top.

title: meatsya pie
directions: *One cup soft bread crumbs or 1/2 cup cracker crumbs may be used instead of dry bread crumbs.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and season salt.
Spread mixture on ham slices.
Roll up and chill.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: zucchini with cheese
directions: Wash zucchini and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
In medium bowl, combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of oregano and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Toss slices in seasoned flour and coat well.
Heat oil in skillet and saute zucchini until golden brown, about 4 minutes on each side.
Drain.
Cover bottom of baking dish with zucchini and top with tomato slices.
Combine sour cream with rest of seasonings.
Spread tomatoes evenly over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured large loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon until lightly brown. Add onion and cook until tender. Add liquor, potatoes, seasonings and clams. Cook about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add milk; heat. Garnish with parsley before serving.

title: cheese stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine first six ingredients with 1 egg.
Combine remaining egg with Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Press 1/3 meat mixture into a 9-inch loaf pan.
Make shallow well lengthwise in center.
Spoon cheese mixture into well.
Cover with remaining meat mixture.
Pat firmly at sides.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done. If desired, top with sliced Provolone cheese and bake for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal crisp
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Mix flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour in ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mary wilson's strawberry jello dessert(serves 12)
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
Chill until slightly jelled.
Add drained and thawed strawberries.
Tear up cake in 1-inch cubes.
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with the cake.
Pour the jello and strawberries over the cake.
Let it chill several hours or overnight.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip before serving.

title: hot dip
directions: In 9 x 13 inch glass pan, spread in order listed. Heat in microwave or 300° oven until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually add
milk and stir until mixed well.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Add some of mixture to egg yolks, mixing well, then add egg yolks to other mixture. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Whip egg whites, adding 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread on pie and brown.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat a little longer with mixer.
On low speed add cinnamon, flour and baking soda. Add vanilla. Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips with wooden spoon.
Put individual pieces of dough on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: mildred welch's famous mincemeat
directions: Boil beef until tender; drain and grind.
When cool, use broth to cook ingredients.
Mix and add salt, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, vinegar and pepper.
Mix and cook 1 hour.
Peel apples and dice while beef is cooking and put the sugar on it and keep stirred.
It makes more natural juice.
Makes 16 pints.
Seal and can.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix and roll in eggs and cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat.

title: baked barley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions, mushrooms and barley in oil.
Stir frequently until barley is lightly browned.
Place in casserole and stir in broth.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yummy apple bread
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add the beaten eggs, salt, flour and vanilla.
Dissolve the baking powder in the sour milk.
Add to other mixture and mix.
Add the apples and chopped nuts.
Place in 2 floured and greased loaf pans.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Beat and pour over the rhubarb mixture.
Bake and cut dough into rhubarb as it bakes.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon pie
directions: Spread butter over bottom of 1 pie shell.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: potato salad with chive blossom vinaigrette
directions: Wash the potatoes and then, without peeling, immerse them in a pan of cold water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, 20 to 25 minutes, depending on their size.
Drain, then run cold water over them until they are cool enough to handle.
Slice them into a salad bowl.
Add the radishes.
Sprinkle lightly with salt. Combine 2 tablespoons chives with the petals of one of the flowers and the oil and vinegar.
Shake well, then pour over the potatoes and radishes and toss.
Add more salt if liked, then scatter on the remaining chives and the petals from a couple of more flowers. Use the rest of the flowers as a garnish.
(The blossoms, which are edible and flavorful, can be omitted, but they look pretty and festive.)
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add onions and peppers.
Add Salad Delight and dressing.
Mix and let chill for 1 hour and serve.

title: peas and celery
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil; simmer until tender.

title: mary ann's special shrimp chowder
directions: Fry until crisp, bacon.
Crumble and set aside.
Saute in bacon drippings, celery, carrots and onions.
When done, stir in flour.
Add water, potatoes and bay leaf.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 20 minutes.
To this, add shrimp and both corns. Simmer until smooth and add milk.
Serve bacon atop each serving. Can be served from a crock-pot.
Can also be made leaving out shrimp.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In a 2-quart glass casserole, microwave beef, garlic and onion on Medium-high for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir once during cooking and drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.

title: weight watchers delight
directions: Layer double graham crackers in casserole dish, small can crushed pineapple (with juice), 1 cup fresh sliced strawberries, 2 sliced bananas, 1 box pudding mix and small Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: pecan soda cracker pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Add mixture to egg whites a little at a time, then fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly for several hours.
Serve with whipping cream or topping.

title: busy day chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken, boil and cool.
Cut up in chunks.
Boil eggs, cool and shell.
Place 1 All-Ready crust in bottom of casserole dish.
Put chicken and cut up eggs in casserole.
In pan, heat butter, chicken broth and soup until blended.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Put pie crust on top.
Cut slits and cook at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes until browned.

title: peach preserve bars
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add egg, beating just until blended.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating until blended.
Press half of crumb mixture into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Spread preserves on crust to within 1/4 inch from edge of pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into bars.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: chocolate butterscotch fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In small microwave bowl place butterscotch chips and 1/3 cup Eagle Brand and set aside. Put chocolate chips, remaining Eagle Brand and vanilla in microwave bowl.
Microwave at High 1 minute and stir until chips are melted. Do same for butterscotch chips and fold in walnuts.
Start with chocolate layer.
Spread evenly the butterscotch over chocolate layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove from pan and cut into squares.

title: fiesta loaf
directions: Cook meat and combine with the rest of the ingredients. Simmer.
Slice bread in half, lengthwise.
Pinch out 2 cups of bread crumbs from both halves.
Mix this with the meat mixture. Fill the hollowed out bread with the meat and crumb mixture; top with Cheddar cheese and place on an ungreased baking sheet to heat.
Let the cheese melt; put top back on loaf to slice.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a gumbo pot mix oil and flour; make a roux.
Add onions and celery; saute well.
Stir in green onions.
Add water and boil slowly for 1 hour.
Add parsley and shrimp; cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add crab meat and oysters.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve over rice.
If okra gumbo is desired, cook down cut up okra until it is not slimy.
Add okra during boiling period.

title: french toast
directions: Cook in a slightly greased skillet until brown, turning once. Serve immediately with syrup, honey or jelly.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together.
Beat egg whites and fold into.
Pour into greased pan.
Melt 1/4 stick butter and pour over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain ground beef and return to skillet.
Add both cans of soup to ground beef (do not add water) and stir over low heat until mixed thoroughly.
Peel potatoes, then cut into cubes.
Put potatoes into pot, fill with water and boil until tender.
Mash the potatoes.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan, layer in order ground beef and soup mixture.
Spread on bottom of pan, next the potatoes.
Then sprinkle the top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and beef mixture bubbles.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mash the yolks.
Add sugar.
Add pepper to taste.
Add Miracle Whip and mustard.
Blend together and fill egg halves.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mince salmon with a fork.
Add crumbs, potatoes, eggs, seasoning and enough milk to moisten.
Shape into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with tomato sauce or creamed peas.

title: cheesy corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts, about 24 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in the olive oil.
Add the celery, carrots and tomatoes.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Add the ham and tomato puree.
Add the broth to thin to the desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

title: old hickory's hush puppies
directions: Put unsifted cornmeal into a bowl.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into this.
Add finely chopped onions. Beat eggs and add the eggs and milk to dry ingredients.
Drop from tablespoon or shape with hands.
Fry hush puppies in deep fat (375°) until brown.
Be sure they are done on the inside before removing from fat.
These are very tasty served with fried fish, coleslaw and hot coffee.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix beans, peas, celery, green pepper, onion and pimientos. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine oil, water, sugar and vinegar.
Marinate vegetables overnight in oil and vinegar mixture.
Drain 1 hour before serving.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a glass bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over layered salad.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise mixture.
Refrigerate covered overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle cheese and bacon on top.
Serves 12.

title: corn pones
directions: Mix together meal, baking powder and salt; cut in lard.
Add enough milk to make a stiff batter. Form into pones with hands or add some more milk and drop from a spoon.
Place in a greased pan. Bake in a hot oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: one-pan potatoes and chicken santa fe
directions: Cut red potatoes into 3/4-inch cubes and microwave 8 to 10 minutes until tender. While potatoes cook, in large skillet toss and brown chicken in oil over high heat 5 minutes. Add potatoes; saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned. Add salsa and corn; toss until heated through. Preparation time: 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.
Contains 300 calories per serving.

title: fluffy salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with crushed pineapple.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Stir well.
This takes a large bowl. Chill until set.

title: lentil cutlets
directions: Whiz lentils
fine. Cook all except tomato sauce; boil. Simmer 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Chill several hours. Slice, bread and
brown
in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, turning once.
Serve with tomato or spaghetti sauce.

title: candy apples
directions: You will need 6 wooden skewers.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Season to taste.
Place in covered baking dish.
Sprinkle rice and chopped peppers over chops.
Mix together soup and milk; pour over rice.
Bake until the rice is well cooked, about 2 hours in 350° oven.
Add more milk if it seems dry.

title: bacon nuts
directions: Cut bacon into 3 parts.
Wrap bacon around chestnuts and put a toothpick in it.
Put in baking pan.
Mix ketchup and sugar together and pour over bacon.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until bacon looks done.

title: rice casserole
directions: Layer in order listed in casserole; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: abbie's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs 1 at a time, add jam and spices.
Add buttermilk and soda, add flour and mix well.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake in layers in 350° oven.
This makes 5 or 6 layers.
You can half this recipe and have a large cake.
This cake freezes well.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Chill. Form into walnut sized balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in saucepan.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture to coat.
Place on waxed paper until firm.
Store in fridge!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and sieve tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook down until thick.
You may can the sauce or freeze it.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 10-inch pie pan with crust, prick bottom with fork and bake 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool. In a large pot of boiling water, add potatoes, carrots, onions and peas.
Cook for approximately 8 minutes.
Drain water, add cooked chicken and set aside.

title: strawberry party cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jell-O, oil and milk.
Add eggs (1 at a time) and mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup each strawberries, nuts and coconut.
Bake
in	13
x 9-inch pan lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.	Cool.

title: no bake peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a large skillet, saute ground beef, onions, garlic, salt and 4 tablespoons of the chili powder.
Puree tomatoes in blender and add to meat mixture.
Add olives and raisins; simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
In a large saucepan, boil water and gradually add cornmeal, stirring constantly to prevent lumping.
Add remaining chili powder; cook and stir until mixture is thickened. Spread meat mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon cornmeal mixture over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour. Sprinkle with cheese during the last 5 to 10 minutes of baking.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Cake:
Mix cake as directed on box.
Drain the mandarin slices and stir into cake batter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake as directed on box.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger. Add onion and green pepper. Mix in the tomato paste and tomato soup.

title: lemon bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.

Cream butter, then add eggs, then stir in alternately milk and dry ingredients and grated rind of one lemon and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. When done, pour piece of one lemon mixed with 1/4 cup sugar and pour over cake and let it cool in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crabmeat burger
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hamburger buns, and mix well. Spread on toasted hamburger buns.
Brown under broiler.
This mixture can also be spread on toast points and served as a cocktail hors d'oeuvre.

title: chili(low-fat)
directions: Brown turkey. Add all other ingredients (except beans).
Put in crock-pot for 8 hours or simmer in pot for 1 hour.
Add beans 30 minutes before serving.

title: festive chicken
directions: Wrap 2 bacon strips around each chicken breast; place in a shallow glass baking dish and set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, combine soy sauce and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken, turning to coat evenly.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, basting occasionally.
Makes 2 servings.

title: toffee
directions: Cook sugars, Karo and water to hard ball stage (254°) and add 1 stick of margarine.
Cook until brittle (300°).
Remove from stove and add chopped nuts.
Pour on greased sheet and cover with half of chocolate.
When chocolate hardens, turn over and spread remaining chocolate on other side.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla wafers.
Add pecans, dates and cherries.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: party punch
directions: Combine sugar and water and heat until sugar has dissolved. Cool and mix this with other ingredients in a large bowl or container.
Pour into gallon jar and store.

title: california veal
directions: Prepare Lemony Vinaigrette and keep warm.

title: sicilian stir-fry
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet or electric frypan over medium heat.
Soak dried tomatoes in hot water (save liquid).
Add nuts to oil in pan and stir-fry until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and stir-fry.
Add prepared greens and stir-fry.
You can add liquid from tomatoes, if needed.
Prepare 20 minutes before serving.
Good with beef, fish or poultry.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add rice and chopped onion; brown 5 minutes.
Put into casserole.
Add 2 cups liquid (consomme, mushroom juice and water).
Mix all together.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese bread rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate one can of crescent rolls and press into a layer in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, saving egg white.
Pour over layer of dough.
Top with other can of crescent rolls layered as before and brush with egg white.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets until soft.
Remove skins and press potatoes through a ricer.
Add salt, eggs, flour, 2/3 cup bread crumbs and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly.
Form mixture into dry balls about the size of walnuts (if mixture is too moist, add more bread crumbs).
Drop balls into boiling, salted water.
When balls come to the surface, boil, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Remove one from liquid and cut open.
If center is dry, they are sufficiently cooked.
Remove balls from liquid.
Serve with gravy, mushroom sauce or onion sauce.
Serves 12.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meringue shells
directions: Combine egg whites, vinegar, vanilla and salt.
Beat until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beat in until stiff peaks form (do not underbeat).
Spoon meringue into six equal portions on ungreased brown bag (paper).
Do not use recycled paper.
Using back of spoon, shape meringues into circles, each about 4 inches in diameter, then shape each circle into a shell (sides should be about 1 1/2 inches high).
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool from draft.
Fill with desired topping (Lemon Topping, recipe included).

title: jeff's dream pie
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding according to directions on box. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crumb crust.
Chill.

title: perky pecans
directions: Beat egg white and cold water until frothy.
Put pecans in egg white mixture.
Coat well. Add sugar mixture and mix well. Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs well; mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, butter, milk and coconut.
Pour into large pie plate and bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and salt with water and work in well until very thick dough is formed.
May need to add extra flour for desired dough.
Roll on heavily floured board until thin dough. Allow to dry approximately 6 to 7 hours, turning one time to dry opposite side.
Add a little more flour to prevent sticking, if necessary.
When dry, cut in very small strips.
Coo 20 to 30 minutes in beef or chicken broth.

title: kookie brittle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest of the recipe to it.
Press into 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle with more nuts, if desired, and press them lightly into the batter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
(Check after 15 minutes so it doesn't burn.)
Cool and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: coconut raisin loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add coconut, raisins, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to coconut/raisins mixture alternately with milk. Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until center tests dry.
Let cool for a few minutes before removing from pan.
Delicious served with any hot beverage.

title: brownie drops
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts, stirring occasionally.
Cook and set aside.
Beat eggs at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until mixture is thick and lemon colored (about 5 minutes).
Add chocolate mixture and next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Press a pecan half into center of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: kraut 'n dumplins
directions: Empty can of kraut in pan with meat seasoning.
Use a tight fitting lid.
Add liquid, enough to steam pastry.
Roll out pastry and place strips on top of kraut.
The steam goes through pastry. Cook slowly.
Good served with pork.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix nonfat dry milk, sugar, salt and water.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with rice and butter.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish, greased, and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Set dish in a shallow pan of water (hot) in preheated 350° oven.
Bake for approximately 1 1/4 hours.
Stir twice after first 1/2 hour of baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Put the lettuce in the bowl first, then add your bell pepper, peas, green onions, celery, shredded carrots and cheese.
Add the Miracle Whip last and then put bacon on the top of the Miracle Whip; put in the refrigerator to chill.
Toss lightly before serving.

title: blueberry cream cheese cake
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, water and blueberries.
Cook while stirring over medium heat until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Cool. Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Press 1/2 of the crumb mixture into the bottom of a foil lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: lemon cloud pie
directions: Beat together pudding mix, sugar, 1/4 cup of the water and the egg in saucepan.
Mix in remaining 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
When completely cooled, whisk lightly, then fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Spread in crumb crust.
Refrigerate until set, about 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place skinned chicken in pan with water.
Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender. Remove chicken and allow to cool, reserving 2 cups broth.
Bone chicken; chop meat.
Combine margarine and stuffing mix.
Combine 1 cup broth with each can of soup.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer 1/3 of stuffing, 1/2 of chicken, mushroom soup mixture, 1/3 of stuffing, remaining 1/2 of chicken, chicken soup mixture and remaining 1/3 of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (may be frozen before baking).
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange in layers in the following order; asparagus, eggs, cheese, soup, and almonds.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to boil sugar, oleo and syrup; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add pinch of soda and vanilla.
Pour over 1 gallon popped popcorn.
Stir until well coated.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and place in baking dish.
Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Stir in rice.
Place meat and rice mixture over cabbage.
Mix the tomato soup and water.
Pour over mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheesy tomato chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and seasonings until smooth.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in half of the cheese at a time.
Stir until completely melted before adding remaining cheese.
Place tomatoes and liquid in blender; cover and puree until smooth.
Stir tomato mixture into soup.
Heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.

title: sweet and saucy apricot ribs
directions: Rub garlic into meaty side of ribs. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in a single layer in a large, shallow baking dish. Pour 1 cup of water into pan and cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick and hot sweet pickles
directions: Put pickles in a large bowl and pour sugar and Tabasco sauce over them. Stir well. Cover and let stand 2 to 3 days at room temperature, stirring 2 to 3 times a day.
Pour into jars and refrigerate.

title: seasons greetings punch
directions: In quart measure or medium bowl, stir sugar into lemon juice. Place ice cubes in large punch bowl, pour in lemon juice and sugar mixture and punch. Slowly add club soda or ginger ale. Stir. If desired, garnish with cherries and orange slices. Now enjoy.

title: quesadillas
directions: Mix together and cook for 10 minutes.
Butter one side of flour tortilla (outside).
Put filling inside fold in half and bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Wash cauliflower and break in florets.
Cook with lemon juice in small amount of boiling water until tender. Drain and whirl cauliflower in
blender until pureed.
Saute onion and celery in butter for 2 to 3 minutes. Blend in flour and stir in broth. Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened. Stir in cauliflower, cream, nutmeg and salt.
Garnish with cheese.
Makes about 1 3/4 quarts or 6 servings.

title: secrets
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oleo and 4 tablespoons coconut.
Cook in double boiler 20 minutes.
Let cool and pour over marshmallows, graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup coconut.
Press in 8-inch pan and frost with plain or chocolate icing.

title: diana's favorite party mix
directions: Combine potato sticks, Cheddar cheese crackers, goldfish shaped crackers, pretzel sticks and pecan pieces in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch
jellyroll
pan;
set
aside.
Combine
butter, Worcestershire
sauce
and
salt;
drizzle
over snack mixture, tossing gently.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Yields 6 1/2 cups.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a large container.

title: cookie jar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl combine all ingredients, except oats, rice cereal, coconut and nuts.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes). By hand, stir in all remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto cookie sheets.
Bake for 13 to 16 minutes or until browned.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: cheesecake (eggless)
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press into 9-inch pie pan and chill.
Beat cream cheese until very soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk; add remaining milk, brown sugar, vanilla and pudding.
Mix as on package.
Pour into crust and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix in corn meal and make well in the center.
Combine egg, milk and melted shortening or oil, then stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°. Cut into squares when done or bake in a bun or muffin pan for 15 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: fruit salad
directions: *Sprinkle with a little lemon or orange juice to keep from turning brown.
Drain before mixing.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Put all of the ingredients, except for the noodles, in a pan and bring to boil.
Boil about 10 minutes.
Add the egg noodles. Cook another 10 minutes or until noodles are limp. (You can add more milk if not juicy enough.)

title: coco lopez coconut cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still warm, poke holes all throughout cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over.
When cool, pour 1 cup of cream of coconut all over cake.
Frost with Cool Whip, then spread on coconut. Refrigerate overnight.
More delicious if stays in refrigerator longer.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In a large bowl, beat the eggs. Add vanilla and gradually add sugar until well blended. Add oil and drained pineapple (reserve juice for frosting). Gradually add the remaining ingredients one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Pour cake mixture into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Place on a wire rack to cool.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar.
Layer in bowl the lettuce, peppers, onions, celery, peas, mayonnaise mixture, Cheddar cheese and bacon. Refrigerate.

title: crab stuffed shrimp
directions: Mix together crabmeat, breadcrumbs, minced garlic, parsley, egg and lemon juice.
Add melted butter until able to hold together.
Shell uncooked shrimp and split.
Stuff with crabmeat stuffing.
Pour melted butter over stuffed shrimp.
Bake at 300° until tails curl (15 to 20 minutes).
Serve with lemon.

title: indiana pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet in oil.
Drain and season.
Place onion and lemon on top of chops and pour sauce and simmer for 45 minutes. Cook uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots and save juice.
Drain pineapple in another container and save juice.
Cut banana into pineapple juice.
Mix pudding in apricot juice until smooth; pour over fruit after removing banana from juice and putting fruit together.
Add pecans to taste.

title: calzone(easter pie)
directions: Filling:
Place drained Ricotta into a large bowl.
Add raw large eggs, parsley, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix with a fork. Slice sausage and add to Ricotta mixture.
After dough has rested, flour board and roll out 1/2 of dough into 9-inch pie pan.
Add 1/2 Ricotta mixture.
Slice 2 hard-boiled eggs.
Place on top of Ricotta mix.
Add remaining Ricotta and the rest of the sliced eggs.
Roll out the other half of the dough.
Place on top of the calzone.
Secure edges of pie and put holes with fork in the top of pie to allow steam to escape.
Beat one egg yolk and brush over top of calzone.
Bake pie in preheated 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal
directions: Place water in microwavable bowl and add oatmeal.
Stir in thoroughly.
Place in microwave for 2 minutes.
Take out of microwave, being careful to use a potholder, as it may be very hot.
Add brown sugar, butter and milk.
Mix together and enjoy a fast, hot breakfast.

title: happy healthy health department
directions: Carefully blend all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Fold in extra portions of kindness, helpfulness and respect for others. Bake at moderate temperature until well seasoned and has a bubbly atmosphere.
Give plenty of patience while waiting to move into our new headquarters.
Sprinkle with togetherness, secret pals and sharing many happy memories and good times in the future.
Serve on a platter of good administration.
Garnish with the finest board members, namely "Grade A" to accompany the Department Main Dish. Add condiments of volunteers who have donated their time and supplies when needed.

title: cabbage and sausage soup
directions: Steam carrots and cabbage until tender.
Add to prepared vegetables the soup and milk.
Slice the sausage and add to mixture.
Cook until blended well.

title: baked potato pancake
directions: Shred potatoes and onion on coarse grater in water.
In large bowl, mix together the rest of ingredients; add drained potatoes and onion.
Mix well.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lemon juice; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add lemon juice.
Serve hot or chill and serve as a spicy punch.

title: molasses candy
directions: Cook in saucepan the sugar, molasses with Karo syrup, butter and vinegar until candy is brittle when tested in cold water (around the hard crack stage on candy thermometer).
Stir in pinch of baking soda when you take off heat.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Make pizza crust as directed.
Brown sausage.
Spread over crust.
Layer hash browns.
Mix 4 eggs and milk; season to taste and pour over pizza.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, except the soup, flour and ground allspice.
Shape into meatballs and roll in flour.
Brown meatballs.
Add undiluted soup.
Cover and let simmer up to 1 hour.

title: world's greatest hot chocolate
directions: Use 2/3 cup per mug.
Add hot water.
Store in airtight container.
May double if you drink a lot.
This stuff is wonderful!!

title: baked apples
directions: Mix and put on top of apples.
Bake until a rich syrup has formed and apples are done.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together.
It's better if made the night before or at least several hours before serving.

title: corn and cheese soup
directions: Combine corn, potatoes, celery, onions, broth and salt.
Boil, then simmer until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine milk and flour.
Blend into vegetables.
Cook until slightly thickened. Add cheese (separate while adding), mustard and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add beer and stir thoroughly.
Serve and top with croutons.

title: roquefort grapes appetizer
directions: In a bowl, combine cheeses and cream and beat smooth.
Drop clean, dry grapes into cheese mixture.
Stir by hand to coat them. Roll in toasted nuts and chill until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Heat all ingredients together in a saucepan until jelly is thoroughly melted.
Whip until smooth.
Place wieners in a dish and cover with sauce. Keeping them warm in a crock-pot works best.

title: beef stew surprise
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 3 hours.
Serves over rice or noodles, as desired.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of plastic wrap.
Flatten using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Dip chicken into egg and dredge in crumbs.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: *For lower fat, lower calorie pie, substitute Carnation lite evaporated skimmed milk.

title: tater wedges
directions: Mix flour and spices to coat potatoes.
Scrub potatoes, leaving the peel on.
Cut into wedges.
Put 4 or 5 wedges in a mixing bag with the flour/spice mixture to coat.
Melt butter in a shallow pan and bake for 30 minutes at 450°.
Turn potatoes after 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Heat butter in a large saucepan.
Add onions and fry 10 minutes.
Add flour and mix until smooth.
Add chicken broth gradually, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Add potatoes, saffron, salt and cayenne pepper; simmer 20 minutes.
Add milk and peas and continue cooking gently for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs and cream cheese together in bowl and gradually add 2 cups of hot soup, beating constantly to avoid curdling.
Return the contents of the bowl to the saucepan and heat, but do not boil.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: tasty braunschweiger spread
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients except peanuts; mix well.
Chill about 15 minutes for easier handling.
Shape into ball; roll in nuts.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or until firm and flavors have blended.
Serve with assorted crackers or small slices of rye bread.

title: honey chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a shallow baking pan in a 375° oven.
Remove from oven and add honey and mustard.
Stir mixture together.
Coat chicken in sauce and place in one layer, meaty side up.
Bake one hour or until done at 375°.

title: pasta sauce with fresh herbs
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions and drain.
In a small saucepan, heat olive oil over low heat.
When oil is hot, but not smoking, remove pan from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Toss with the pasta.
Sprinkle with fresh Parmesan cheese and serve at once.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetable dippers or chips.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan with 1/2 package tortillas.
Brown beef; season to taste with salt, garlic salt and chili powder.
Spread over tortillas.
Spread beans next, then the cheese.
Place rest of tortillas in pan.
Mix chicken soup with tomatoes in a bowl.
Pour over top, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and onion.
Cook broccoli until almost done.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer broccoli, 1/2 sauce, chicken and remainder of sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Salt and pepper ground round and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with soup.
Sprinkle with Tater Tots.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: quick-fix biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil to milk and pour into dry mix. Stir until mixture makes a ball and cleans the bowl sides.
Knead 8 to 10 times on waxed paper without additional flour.
Roll to 1/4 to 1/2 inch thickness as desired.

title: lentil soup
directions: Simmer ingredients for an hour or so, then add cooked potatoes and carrots, about 2 cups diced potatoes and 1 cup diced carrots. Add water to soup to taste.
Cook for about another 30 minutes or so.

title: linda's pecan custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients except pecans and pastry.
Beat until well blended (I use mixer).
Add pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 40 minutes longer or until filling is firm. (Baking time is usually closer to 50 to 60 minutes longer; watch it very closely during last 10 to 15 minutes.
Pie will puff up and split open; filling should be very firm when you gently shake it.)

title: micro peanut brittle
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes on High, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto well buttered cookie sheet.
Pull to thin out when cool enough to touch.
Makes 1 pound.

title: terry's special
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain.
Add pork and beans and heat to boiling.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: marian's peanut butter candy
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together thoroughly; press down evenly in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt together the chocolate chips and 6 tablespoons butter or margarine over low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over first mixture.
Let set until firm.
Cut into size pieces desired.
(Very rich and delicious.)

title: crisscross cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat in eggs. Add cream and flavorings.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Chill. Roll 1/4 of the dough at a time, 1/8-inch thick on surface sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Cut as desired.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread with Date Filling, leaving 1/4-inch edges.
Cut narrow strips from dough scraps. Crisscross over Filling, pressing ends to bottom of cookies.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Makes 50 servings.

title: nut goodies
directions: Melt butter, chips and peanut butter.
Add peanuts and marshmallows and mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keep refrigerated.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: banana split pie
directions: Prepare pudding by box instructions.
Drain pineapple; slice bananas.
Mix pecans into pudding.
Make layers of bananas and pudding with pineapple mixed in.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: gladys' hot rolls
directions: Mix
water,
sugar and yeast;
let
stand
minutes. Then mix the rest of ingredients to make
a
soft
dough.
Let stand in a warm place until double in bulk.	Punch down.
Make into rolls any size or shape.	Let raise until double in size. Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
This
dough
makes good cinnamon rolls, too.

title: tasty jello
directions: Mix in order; cool slightly.
Mix again to blend fully.
Can be put in mold.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni and vegetables.
Combine seasonings with mayonnaise, sour cream and vinegar.
Blend with macaroni and vegetables.
Chill until ready to serve.
Garnish with egg slices.

title: open tacos
directions: Brown and season meat.
Heat 2 sauces in small pan.
(If can't find El Patio, use taco sauce and leave off tomato sauce.)
Pour small amount of oil in same skillet and heat.
Heat tortillas one at a time in oil.
Turn once, just take seconds, keep soft.
Drain on paper towel.
Dip in hot sauce.
Put a layer of meat, onion and cheese on taco.
Repeat and add lettuce and tomato on top.
Your can add olives, avocado, etc.
Serve with Ranch Style beans.

title: 24 hour omelet
directions: Trim crusts from bread slices and butter bread on one side. Cut bread slices into about 1-inch cubes.
Place buttered side up in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex or glass cake pan.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread slices.
Add cubes of ham or sausage on top with grated cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, in a preheated 325° oven about 1 1/2 hours or until egg mixture is set.
Ten minutes before done, uncover.

title: bobbie's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with crackers.

title: broccoli rice and cheese casserole
directions: Saue onion in butter.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili meat deluxe
directions: Cook ground beef until crumbly.
Add onions, tomatoes, peppers and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Put layer of meat and layers of macaroni in a greased casserole dish.
Let the top be meat.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: lime mist
directions: Combine lime gelatin and applesauce.
Heat over low heat until gelatin dissolves and then cool.
Stir in celery, nuts, maraschino cherries and lemon-lime carbonated beverage.
Chill until syrupy. Chill Carnation evaporated milk in tray until ice crystals form. Whip until stiff and add lemon juice; whip until very stiff.
Fold into gelatin mixture and chill until firm.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in airtight container.
When ready to use, mix 2 teaspoons or to taste in 1 cup of hot water.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt margarine and vanilla in pan.
Mix sugar and cocoa well in bowl.
Add margarine and vanilla to sugar and cocoa.
Mix well. Add peanut butter and mix well.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut and serve.

title: tita's meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Shape into meatballs.
Fry meatballs in olive oil until golden brown.
Makes 30 meatballs.
Delicious served with Tita's Spaghetti Sauce below.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together well and put into baking dish and bake until bubbly.
Bake at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
(Be sure that eggs are at room temperature before using.)
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix well, then add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased, foil-covered cookie sheet.
Place cookies in oven and immediately turn oven off.
Leave cookies in closed oven overnight or until oven is completely cool.
Yields approximately 2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate praline layer cake(one 2 layer cake)
