directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 (8 or 9-inch) round pans. Combine butter, whipping cream and brown sugar in small heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat just until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Pour evenly into prepared pans.
Sprinkle evenly with chopped pecans.
Combine cake mix, oil, water and eggs in large bowl; beat at low speed until moistened, then beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Carefully spoon batter over praline mixture in pans.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool layers in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove to racks to cool completely.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients except egg whites; beat thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed bacon rolls
directions: Combine everything but bacon.
Cut bacon strips in half. Shape mixture into balls.
Wrap in bacon strips.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place on wire racks over baking pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until bacon is brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and stir well.

title: merr's barbecue spareribs sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Recipe may be doubled or tripled. Baste spareribs with sauce as they barbecue.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Remove tails.
Melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in garlic.
Saute, but do not brown.
Add shrimp; saute 1 to 2 minutes on each side until shrimp is pink and skin is opaque.
Pour lemon juice over.
Salt and pepper.
Remove onto plate.
Keep juices in.
Stir in parsley and boil.
Pour over shrimp.
Serve with wild rice.

title: brandy balls
directions: Mix in order listed.
Roll into 1-inch balls; store in airtight container.
These are best if allowed to ripen and mellow for a couple of days before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in half of butter until soft.
Stir in flour. Add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture thickens. Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and eggs; mix gently with broccoli.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with crackers; dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients for filling, add pecans last. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 mins.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30-35 mins. or longer.
Outer edges of filling should be firm, center should be slightly soft.

title: raystown lobster
directions: Bring to a
boil
water,
vinegar,
salt and seasoning. Add fish, keep to a boil
and cook for 25 minutes.
Drain, and serve with melted butter.

title: vegetable breakfast casserole
directions: Slightly beat eggs and milk, then add melted butter. Set aside.

title: australian pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from steak. Cut into thin strips. Brown meat, onion and garlic in butter & oil in large skillet. Add salt, celery salt, pepper, tomatoes, bouillon cube and green pepper. Cover and simmer 30-45 minutes or until meat is tender. Combine cornstarch and Worcestershire sauce; stir into meat mixture. Cook until thickened. Serve with cooked rice or noodles. 6 servings.

title: baked onion soup
directions: Sprinkle French bread with celery powder and brown in broiler. Cut onion in half and slice in thin pieces.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add water and bouillon.
Simmer until hot. Put soup in crock.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: holiday fudge(makes approximately 3 pounds.)
directions: Combine sugar,	margarine
and	milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to	a
full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes
over
medium
heat, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate bits until melted.
Add
Marshmallow
Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour
into
well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.

title: crumb cake
directions: Take flour, sugar and butter and rub to crumbs.
Take out one cup of crumbs for top.
To all the rest, add a mixture of egg, cinnamon, buttermilk (or sour milk) and soda.
Spread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and eggs. Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder. Mix well. Add corn flakes and coconut. Drop by teaspoon on sprayed cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: herb buttered french bread
directions: In a small bowl, combine butter (margarine) paprika, rosemary, marjoram and parsley, mixing until well blended.
Spread mixture on French bread slices.
Wrap in foil.
Heat in oven.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples in pastry lined pan.
Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg in saucepan.
Add orange juice and butter; heat until butter is melted.
Pour over apples.
Cover with pastry strips. Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: golden broccoli bake
directions: Cook fresh broccoli, covered in a small amount of boiling water for 9-11 minutes or till crisp-tender.
Drain.
Transfer to a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Combine soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise, and pimiento.
Stir into broccoli.
Top with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or till heated through.
Serves 6.

title: earthquake cake
directions: * Ingredients listed on cake mix package.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes and taco mix in microwavable dish.
Microwave on high until cheese is almost melted.
Place meat in dish and finish melting cheese. Eat with tortilla chips -- enjoy.

title: crock pot pizza
directions: Brown meat with onions. Cook noodles. Layer in crock pot: beef, noodles, sauce, pepperoni and cheese. Start again with beef. Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: barbecue
directions: Mix all well.
Add small amount of water.
Cover meat mixture and simmer about an hour.
Add 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: easy tamale casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 16-inch pan.
Spread rice on bottom, then spread chili over the rice.
Cut each tamale in half, lengthwise. Arrange on top of chili.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° until hot and bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate wet cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in bowl.
Bring margarine, cocoa, oil and water to boil in a saucepan.
Pour over the sugar and flour mixture, mixing well.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased.
Bake at 400° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Stir baking powder into flour.
Add flour mixture, alternating with milk; mix well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in pineapple.
Spray tube pan with cook spray and pour batter into pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turkey chili
directions: Sear ground turkey and onion in skillet. Drain off any grease. Put in saucepan and add salt, pepper, chili powder, Ro-Tel and tomatoes.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Add the beans.
Cook 15 more minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Fritos and lettuce.
Refrigerate for several
hours (overnight if possible) before serving.
Then break up lettuce and add Fritos.
Add to refrigerated mixture. Mix and serve.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and Pet milk to soft ball stage.
Add the chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla and stir until smooth, then add pecans; stir well.
Makes approximately 5 pounds of fudge.
(Nestle chocolate chips make a better fudge.)

title: easy fudge
directions: Boil for 5 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons vanilla.
Cool and beat; add nuts.

title: grande guacamole
directions: Avocados should be soft and rotten looking.
Peel and pit avocados, then mush with a fork.
Mix in rest of ingredients and eat.
It won't keep, so eat it all.
Good with tortilla chips or Doritos.

title: soft honey sugar cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat Baker's Deluxe margarine, sugar, honey, egg and vanilla extract until thoroughly blended.
Blend in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cover; chill dough at least 2 hours.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut dough with cookie cutters into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets; cool on wire racks.
Decorate as desired.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Put in crock-pot and cook for 12 hours.
Makes 5 pints.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Separate the yolks from the whites of the eggs.
Add flour to the yolks gradually, then thin it down with oil and milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Beat well until like thick cream.
Leave to stand for 1/2 hour, then stir in the stiffly beaten egg whites and mix well.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, rice, lemon juice, soup and salad dressing together; refrigerate.
Put salad in baking dish; top with chopped eggs, grated cheese and crumbled potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until heated through.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: susie's homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook down until thick.
Pour into cans and seal.
Ideal for home gardeners.

title: fruit slush
directions: Thoroughly mix together all ingredients.
Freeze.
Allow mixture to thaw slightly to a slush texture before serving.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients (either pressure cooker 5 minutes or microwave 25 minutes); set aside.

title: strawberry jello salad(for 9 x 13-inch dish)
directions: Dissolve both packages jello in boiling water in mixing bowl or saucepan.
Add strawberries; cut them up as they thaw.
Add the undrained pineapple and mashed bananas.
Stir to mix.
Pour 1/2 of jello mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Mix sour cream and pecans and spread over first layer of jello.
Pour remaining jello mixture over the top of sour cream layer.
Refrigerate until set.

title: split pea soup(serves 12)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot with a tight fitting lid. Bring to a rolling boil and skim off any foam that rises to the surface. Cover. Simmer 2 hours. Adjust seasoning.

title: coconut crisp
directions: Roll into balls.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Layer tortillas in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon in chicken mixture; spread.
Add a layer of tortillas; then cheese.
Repeat, ending with tortillas topped with cheese.
You can add Parmesan cheese also (optional).
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Combine drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight.
Beat pineapple juice, egg, flour, vinegar and sugar; heat until thick, stirring constantly. Refrigerate until completely cooled.
When cooled, mix sauce and Cool Whip.
Add nuts, marshmallow mixture and apples.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: crab melt-away
directions: Mix all ingredients (except muffins).
Spread 1/2 inch thick on muffin halves.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Cut into quarters with pizza cutter.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Can freeze for 3 months.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar of hearts into frying pan.
Drain other jar.
Chop all hearts and set aside.
Add onion and garlic to frying pan and saute until onion is limp, about 5 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Mix first 4 items. Put marshmallows on top.
After if jells, use Cool Whip and mayonnaise to spread on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Let set overnight.

title: tuna and pasta
directions: Cover pan with olive oil.
Let oil heat, then put in pan the chopped onion, mushrooms (drain can), garlic powder, basil, salt, pepper and pat of butter. Saute until onion fries clear.
Put in whole can of tuna and water also from tuna.
Add 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Turn off. Do not overcook tuna. Cook pasta; drain.
Put in big pasta bowl or back in pot.
Put tuna mixture over pasta and mix well.
Let sit about 5 minutes for flavor.
WaLa!

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute onions in small amount of butter.
Mix with Cheez Whiz and
sour
cream.
Melt
butter; mix cheese with butter, then
add sour cream.
Put frozen Tater Tots in greased baking sheet.
Pour cheese
mixture
over tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer.
Let set overnight for better flavor.

title: frangos
directions: Melt chocolate; set aside to cool slightly.
Cream the butter and sugar, then add to cooled chocolate.
Beat until fluffy.
Add whole eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add peppermint and vanilla; beat again.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the crumbs in paper lined muffin cups.
Add chocolate mixture; sprinkle remainder of crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until firm.
Better if made the day before serving.
Top with whipped cream and maraschino cherries.
Very rich!!

title: cream cheese fruit pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla extract and condensed milk until smooth.
Add lemon juice and mix again.
Add the Cool Whip.
Mix in pie filling being careful not to overmix.
Pour mixture into the 2 pie crusts and refrigerate for about 3 hours.

title: chili pie
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet; drain off excess grease.
Add chili, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/2 cup of water; let simmer 15 minutes.
Place nacho chips on plate.
Spoon meat sauce over chips.
Sprinkle on meat, onion, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Cover with cheese.
Put in microwave for 45 seconds or until cheese begins to melt.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and place in greased baking dish.
Top
with 1 cup crushed cornflakes and 1 cup chopped almonds. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Put the cider in a crock-pot.
Add the red hots; let simmer for about 1 hour.
Pour and serve with a cinnamon stick, if desired.

title: bacon, onion and potatoes
directions: Place
bacon
in
12-inch
Dutch
oven	and cook for 15 minutes until
bacon is crisp.
Add onions, cover and cook for 10 minutes
until
onions are limp.
Mix potatoes with onions and bacon,
cover
and cook, stirring once until potatoes are tender when
pierced
with a fork, about 25 minutes.
Drain or spoon out grease.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Frost Carrot Cake.

title: toffee bars
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla together; mix in sifted flour. Add chocolate chips. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake. Cut into squares while warm. Chill before serving.

title: jon's fudge
directions: Into a heavy, buttered, 2-quart saucepan, add sugar, milk, syrup, salt and chocolate, stirring constantly over medium heat until chocolate melts.
Reduce heat; cook until mixture forms a soft ball (232°), stirring only when necessary.
Remove from heat immediately and set pan in cold water.
Add butter, but don't stir.
When mixture cools to 180° (pan bottom warm to touch), add vanilla and beat vigorously by hand, without stopping, until mixture starts to lose gloss.
Immediately pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Score into squares with knife.

title: broiled flank steak a l'orange
directions: In a bowl, combine Italian dressing, orange peel, orange juice and dill weed.
Score the flank steak slightly on both sides.
Pour the dressing mixture over the steak and marinate at least two hours.
Reserve the marinade and place the steak on a broiler pan sprayed with a non-stick oil.
Broil the steak 4 inches from the heat for 5 minutes.
Turn and broil 4 minutes longer for rare, or longer for desired doneness.
Remove from the broiler to rest.
Simmer the reserved marinade and vegetables for 5 minutes.
Slice the steak diagonally and serve topped with the reserved marinade and the vegetables.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Then add brown sugar, sugar, shortening, eggs, baking soda, baking powder, salt and flour.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients.
Add tea last. Fold in berries.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan or make into muffins.
Bake at 350° about 28 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin sauce(for ham)
directions: Combine the raisins, water and marmalade.
Bring to a boil. Mix the sugar, cornstarch, salt and cloves with the raisin mixture.
Cook and simmer until thick.
Serve with ham.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Clean and trim vegetables. Slice thinly. Mix other ingredients and beat. Pour over vegetables and toss well.
Let set overnight or several hours before serving.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Serve with Tostitos, sour cream, avocado slices, jalapeno peppers, green onions, Monterey Jack cheese and picante sauce.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Chop onion.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat. Ladle into serving bowls and sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits on top.

title: pork chops, peas and carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Brown pork chops. Place in bottom of casserole dish. Add sliced onions on top of meat, then add carrots (slice and precook separately in water and drain). Add peas, tomato soup and 1/2 cup water. Bake 2 1/2 hours. First 1/2 hours, covered and last hour, uncovered.

title: apple bars
directions: Cut dough to pea size and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: snack mix
directions: Combine cereal, pretzels and crackers in a large plastic bag. Pour oil over mixture. Seal bag and toss to coat. Add seasoning mix. Seal bag and toss again until well coated. Makes 10 cups.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Cook peas until done, do not overcook.
Chill peas for several hours or overnight.
Combine peas with rest of ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix in large bowl the eggs, Crisco and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Store in covered container in the fridge.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
This can be kept in fridge for 6 weeks.

title: peach cake
directions: Line greased pan with peaches and juice.
Sprinkle on brown sugar and dry cake mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add eggs.
Beat well. Stir in flour and salt.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to batter, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and apples.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle on topping (recipe follows).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until done.

title: two-corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and cottage cheese until smooth.
Stir in corn; set aside.
In large bowl, mix all other ingredients together. Combine with egg mixture; stir just until blended.
Bake in muffin pan at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: banana pudding
directions: Slice bananas.
Layer bananas and vanilla wafers in a bowl. In another bowl, mix instant pudding and 1/2 of the milk asked for on the pudding box directions.
Add condensed milk to pudding mixture and Cool Whip; mix.
Pour this mixture over cookies and bananas.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning with flour.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese, mixing all ingredients with hands.
Shape into small balls or patties.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: applesauce peach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; chill until partially set. Stir in applesauce, pecans and peach slices.
Turn mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until set 3 to 4 hours.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Slowly add water and oil.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until stiff.
Let cool and knead.
Store in Ziploc bags or containers.
You can add food coloring, tempera paint, Kool-Aid, pumpkin spice, glitter or flavor extracts to the liquid for color and/or fragrance.

title: white cake chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: fide's spicy chicken potato casserole
directions: On skillet, place following items in the following order: chicken, potatoes, chicken bouillon, salsa del pato and salt. Place on range; cover and simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve hot with flour or corn tortillas.
Serves about 8.

title: heavenly pumpkin pie
directions: Soften	gelatin
in cold water.
Place in top of double boiler the
pumpkin,
milk, egg yolks, salt, sugar and spice. Cook 10 minutes over boiling water, stirring constantly.
Stir in gelatin.
Chill until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 1/2
cup
sugar
gradually.
Fold pumpkin, vanilla and Cool
Whip into egg whites.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
Top with more Cool Whip.
This is scrumptious!

title: kentucky pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: any flavor jello mold
directions: *May use diet Jell-O too.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in bacon drippings.
Add pork and beans, tomato paste, tomato juice, bell pepper, salt, pepper and garlic. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Top with bacon strips.

title: honey-peanut dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Especially good with banana or other mild fruit salads.
Makes 1/2 cup dressing.

title: smelt, italian style
directions: Cook onion and garlic in melted fat or oil until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, salt, sugar and pepper; mix well.
Cover and cook slowly about 30 minutes until slightly thickened and flavors blend.
Stir often during cooking. Stir in parsley.
Spread sauce over bottom of 2 or 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Arrange smelt in a single layer on sauce down the center of baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and cheeses.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Serves 6.

title: fold-over tortilla bake
directions: Cook beef and pour off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, enchilada sauce, cumin, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes. Pour half of meat sauce into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Place in a baking dish prepared as for a souffle baker. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake the corn for about 1/2 hour.

title: susan's super vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot or large crock-pot, combine all the ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add cut up fresh broccoli and sliced zucchini.
Simmer just until broccoli and zucchini are tender.

title: monterey fondue bake(meatless main dish)
directions: Spread bread slices with butter or margarine.
Cut bread in 1/2-inch cubes; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine milk, eggs, salt and several dashes of hot pepper sauce; stir in bread cubes, cheese, corn and chilies.
Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Let stand for 1 hour at room temperature.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean in center.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together and fold in strawberries. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: barbecued baby back ribs
directions: Place ribs in large roasting pan. Cover. Bake in 400-degree oven for 30 minutes. Drain fat from ribs. Reduce heat to 325 degree. Return ribs cover, to oven for 1 hour. Drain fast again. Mix chili sauce, brown sugar, lemon juice, vinegar and onion. Pour over ribs. Cover and return to oven bake at 350 degree for 2-3 hours.

title: honey-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and honey, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and ginger; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and dates, mixing well.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets; bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: lamb on skewers(arni souv lakia, greek name)
directions: Cut the onions into quarters and separate the layers.
Cut the peppers into quarters and cut each quarter in half.
Combine all ingredients, except tomatoes, in a shallow roasting pan; mix so that the meat is completely coated.
Marinate in the refrigerator for several hours (overnight is better).
Before cooking, add tomatoes to the marinade and mix well to coat with the juices.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix oleo, Coca-Cola, Wesson oil and cocoa and bring to boil. Do not cook.
Remove from heat and add miniature marshmallows; stir until dissolved.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Melt in double boiler the caramels, water and oleo. Gradually add hot caramel sauce to eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla, stirring well.
Add pecans.
Bake in uncooked pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to cook for 40 minutes more.

title: luau chicken
directions: Make marinade of soy sauce, lime juice, onion and garlic. Marinate chicken 3 to 4 hours.
Remove from marinade; sprinkle with 5 spice and brush melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes and sprinkle with 5 spice 15 minutes before baking is done.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Heat juice to just below boiling.
Pour over Jell-O and stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Let cool.
Add Coke, cherries and pineapple.
Put in refrigerator. When Jell-O begins to thicken, chip up cream cheese into Jell-O and add pecans.
Pour into mold and return to refrigerator until it gels.

title: chocolate pie(aunt beulah's)
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until thick, constantly stirring, over medium heat.
Set off.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Brown crust and have cooled.
Whip egg whites for meringue.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar.
Pour filling into crust; cover with meringue.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix unsweetened applesauce, lard and butter, salt, nutmeats and soda together.
Add sugar, egg, flour and baking powder.
Mix well, then add the cinnamon, cloves and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake in 300° oven until brown.

title: tuna st. jacques
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Brown onions and mushrooms in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Combine soup and vermouth and bring to a boil.
Add half of the sauce to onion/mushroom mixture.
Spoon equally into 6 buttered sea shells or ramekins.
Top with parsley and chunks of tuna.
Spoon on the remainder of sauce.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs and sprinkle over each serving.
Drizzle a small amount of melted butter over crumbs.
Heat in oven for 10 minutes or until browned.
Serves 6.

title: apple chess pie
directions: Combine egg, sugar, margarine and flour.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and apples.
Pour into pie shell.
Do not use top crust over filling.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: "no fail" pie crust(makes 2 pies or 4 single)
directions: Cut in shortening and flour.
Make well and add egg, vinegar and ice water that have been mixed together.
Mix all together with tips of fingers slowly and sparingly.
Divide and roll out with flour dusting.

title: erika's easy stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients together.
Spoon mixture into hollowed out peppers.
Place in microwave dish.
Add about 1/2 cup water. Microwave on High for about 30 to 40 minutes, rotating once.

title: tira mi su
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar in 2-quart saucepan on medium speed about 30 seconds or until well blended.
Beat in milk.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low; boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Place plastic wrap directly onto milk mixture in saucepan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until cool.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Mix mayo, cheese and oregano in bowl.
Place chicken in baking dish and pour mixture over and bake at 375° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: sandies
directions: Mix (cream) butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla, mixing well.
Add flour and pecans.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
Form in crescents and bake on cookie sheet for about 20 minutes at 325°.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: coconut-cheese balls
directions: Melt butter in small skillet.
Add coconut and stir until well blended.
Place cream cheese in a medium bowl; stir and add coconut mixture.
Mix; chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll the balls in the additional coconut.
Chill until serving time. Leftover balls, frozen, can be kept indefinitely.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. As soon as cake comes out of the oven, poke holes all over the cake with a fork and pour topping on while hot.

title: robin long's cabbage casserole
directions: Soak cabbage in cold water 2 to 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and milk; bring to a boil.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix crushed corn flakes with margarine; spread in bottom of baking dish (save some to use on top).
Put cabbage over corn flakes.
Add soup mix; top with remaining corn flakes.

title: angel torte
directions: Combine dry milk, sugar and coffee; mix together. Beat egg yolks and add water; add to dry mixture. Add butter and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened; then cook 2 minutes longer. Add flavorings and beat until thick enough to spread. Spread filling over each layer. Sprinkle with nuts and stack.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream 1 stick margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add 4 eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with large can of chocolate syrup.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well and pour in a sheet pan.
Bake approximately 35 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes before icing.

title: apple raisin cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda; mix well. Add apples, chocolate chips and raisins. Bake at 350° in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan 40 to 45 minutes.

title: angel food custard cake
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and milk until thick, like custard. Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla, almond extract and marshmallows.
Cool.
Break up an angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour custard over cake.
Spread La Creme whipped topping over cake.
Cover with Angel Flake coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Heat milk and let cool to lukewarm.
Add brown sugar, salt, pepper, flour, eggs and melted margarine.
Cook carrots until soft; drain and blend.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart, round, greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, eggs, food coloring and vanilla. Cream again.
Sift flour and add rest of dry ingredients.
Sift again; combine with sugar mixture, along with soda, buttermilk and vinegar.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely before frosting.

title: word perfect strawberry ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients into an ice cream maker.
Turn the handle until the ice cream is firm.
Get yourself a big bowl and enjoy.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill.
Cut into slices and bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: marinated fish (escabeche)
directions: Coat the fish pieces all over with flour.
Heat oil in skillet and when hot, fry the fish pieces.
Remove fish and set aside, then fry the sliced onions and peppers in the same skillet.
In a crock or other vessel, combine the fish pieces, onion and peppers, the capers, salt, pepper, paprika and olives.
Cover with equal amounts of oil and vinegar.
Close tightly and allow to marinate for a week or more before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over raspberry Jell-O and mix, then add cup of juice.
Let set in refrigerator.
Right before it jells, when it is just starting to get thick, add cranberries, then add the apples, celery and nuts.

title: yogurt shake(for diabetics)
directions: Place all ingredients except yogurt in bowl and mix well. Chill at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Put mixture and yogurt into blender and blend until smooth. Serve cold.

title: jan hagel
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Blend flour and cinnamon.
Stir into butter mixture.
Pat into pan.
Beat water and egg white until frothy; brush over dough and sprinkle with nuts. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Cut immediately into finger-like strips.
Makes 50 (3 x 1-inch) strips.

title: apple crumble
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch square or 10 x 6-inch rectangular baking dish.
Arrange apples in dish.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and egg until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: cashew chicken appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, in a large bowl.
With a teaspoon, scoop out enough of the mixture to form a ball.
Shape each ball carefully and then roll it in the chopped cashews. Chill.
Yields approximately 20 appetizers.

title: christmas six layer cookies
directions: You will also need a glass pan with greased sides.

title: easy chicken salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add 1 small can of shoestring potatoes.
Add slivered almonds.
Serves 8.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in flour. Add coconut; mix all this into batter.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in tube pan.
As soon as removed from oven, pour a mixture of orange juice and powdered sugar over cake.
Let stand in pan overnight.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Toss the spaghetti and oil together. Add the eggs and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Pour into a greased 10-inch deep dish pie plate, forming crust.

title: chicken milano
directions: Prepare rice; keep warm.
Remove skin and bones from chicken. Cut into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, saute onion and garlic in hot butter.
Add chicken.
Cook until lightly browned on all sides.
Add tomato soup and remaining items. Over high heat, heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Spoon over rice.
Serve in deep platter.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles; fold in cottage cheese, sour cream and onion.
Set aside.
Cook meat until no longer pink and drain; add tomato sauce and seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon half of noodle mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole and top with half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: cheese strata
directions: Trim crust and butter bread. Cut bread into quarters.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch buttered dish.
Top with cheese.
Add another layer of bread and cheese; have 2 layers. Whip mustard, salt, milk and eggs.
Pour over bread.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes. Cut in small squares for appetizers or cut into large 4 x 4-inch squares for lunch. Serve lukewarm or cooled.

title: tomato consomme
directions: To peel the tomatoes, dip them in the boiling water for a few seconds and slip off the skins.
Cut in half.
Press and seed and dice into about 1/2-inch cubes.
Bring broth to a boil.
Add diced tomatoes.
Remove from heat immediately and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix the 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon; roll balls in mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes; remove from baking sheet.

title: pina colada bread pudding(with rum sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt butter in 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Pour the combined cream of coconut and milk (4 cups total) over the bread. Stir in pecans and coconut. Combine eggs, pineapple, vanilla and sugar. Mix well and combine with bread mixture. Pour into baking pan. Bake for about an hour. Serve with Rum Sauce.

title: louisiana pralines
directions: Mix evaporated milk and sugar and cook until mixture will form a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add butter and vanilla. Remove from heat and beat until cool.
Add the pecans and crop on greased cookie sheet immediately.
Allow to cool completely.

title: two-layer salad
directions: Refrigerate until it starts to jell.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring water to boil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add salt, white
pepper,	garlic powder and shredded cheese.
Stir until cheese
melts.
Add
half
and
half
and butter.
Stir and heat to boiling.	Slowly add water to flour, stirring constantly, until texture	is
smooth.
Slowly add to hot mixture, stirring rapidly.	Cook
and
stir
until soup is the consistency of heavy cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: butter chip pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in pan; add salt.
Pack with ice.
Drain ice and water after 3 hours.
Add other ingredients and heat to boiling or until yellow.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Sift flour and baking powder; then add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix egg, sugar, butter and milk with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons into hot fat.
Shake in a bag of 10x sugar while warm.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In large mix-n-store pitcher, combine eggs and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add egg mixture and beat until smooth.
Test for thickness; add more milk if too thick or flour if too thin.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Beat well.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 300° for 20 or 30 minutes.
Store in Tupperware with wax paper between layers.
Can freeze.
They are good keepers.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to the batter.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and cool.
Roll in a mixture of egg and water, then roll in a mixture of flour and corn meal.
Reroll potatoes into each mixture the second time.
Fry in margarine on medium heat. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on platter.
Drain shrimp; put on cheese, then picante sauce and chopped jalapeno peppers on top.
Serve with corn chips or saltines.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together thoroughly the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in sour cream and grated bananas.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Let stand for 20 minutes before baking. Bake until it tests done. Serve warm or cold.
Enjoy!

title: raisin bars
directions: Bring raisins and next 5 ingredients to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sift the dry ingredients; add to raisin mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread on greased cookie sheet (not too thick).
Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Frost, if desired.

title: lucky if you get a bite
directions: Mix together flour and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until tan.
Cool.
Mix together and spread over crust, cream cheese, 9 ounces Cool Whip and confectioners sugar. Mix together and spread over cream cheese layer, pudding and milk. Top with 9 ounces Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt Crisco and both kinds of morsels in microwave for approximately 2 minutes or until morsels can be stirred smooth. Pour in peanuts and stir.
You can add more peanuts until all the chocolate is gone.
Spoon on wax paper and let sit for a few hours until dry.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill until firm.

title: winter soup
directions: Cook meat in
large
pot until tender.	Remove meat and wash pot or
use
another
pot.	To
the
meat,	add tomatoes, onions, green pepper,
carrots and corn.
Cook for 30 minutes. Add black pepper,
garlic,
salt,
okra, string beans and lima beans.
Cook for 30 minutes longer.
Salt to your taste.

title: nourishing infant formula
directions: To make barley water, put one cup barley in cheese cloth and tie loosely in 2-quarts pure water.
Use pure water for the chlorine content could cause allergies.
Boil for 6 hours; add more water and boil down to 15 ounces of barley.

title: linzer squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg gradually, tossing with fork until flour mixture is moistened.
Shape into ball, flatten slightly.
On floured surface, roll 2/3 of dough into a 16 x 11-inch rectangle. Place in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan (dough should go up sides).
Spread pie filling on dough.
Roll remaining dough 1/4-inch thick; cut strips 1/2-inch wide.
Crisscross strips over filling.
Press ends to border.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool in pan.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix well. Cook in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour. Let set for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray muffin tin with vegetable oil spray.

title: cajun stew with polish sausage
directions: Put pepper, onion and tomatoes into a large pot; cook for 15 minutes.
Add spices, shrimp, chicken, sausage and rice; simmer for 30 minutes, covered.
Can be thickened with 1 tablespoon flour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats.
Let stand.
Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir.
Add oats and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the sherbet.
Chill.
Just before serving, add sherbet.

title: orange stuff
directions: Drain all fruit.
Cream together cream cheese and dry Jell-O. Add Cool Whip and mix until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: sugarless no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Place margarine, milk and cocoa in pan. Heat until boiling, stirring continuously. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, Equal and oats. Stir in vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Cool in freezer. Yields 50 cookies.

title: penny's easy brownies(excellent!!  and easy!)
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients, mixing after each addition.
Pour into greased 9 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Bake at 275° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Brown garlic, basil, parsley, salt and pepper in oil.
Add clams with juice and cook for 20 minutes.
Serve over linguine.

title: old time banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add egg yolks.
Mix real good. Add milk a little at a time so it will mix good.
Add vanilla. Cook over low heat till thick.
Put a layer of wafers on bottom of dish (2 quart dish) then put a layer of sliced bananas, add about half of the mixture over bananas.
Put another layer of wafers and bananas.
Pour the rest of the mixture over this.

title: italian green beans
directions: Cook onions and garlic until opaque (never dark).
Add tomatoes and salt.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add green beans; cook until heated through.
(In a rush, you can use spaghetti sauce without meat and heat.)

title: cold avocado soup
directions: In
electric
blender,
beat avocado, consomme and onion juice at
high speed 5 seconds.
In mixing bowl, beat in cream and sour cream, salt and pepper.
Chill.
Garnish with paprika, parsley and scallions.

title: herb vegetable soup
directions: Mix herbs and add to tomatoes with sugar and garlic.
Mix well and cover; let stand in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, add water and vegetables.
Bring all to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer over very low heat for 3 hours.
Add rice and cook for 20 more minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 8 to 10 cups.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix cornstarch with a little milk.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sugar, salt, mustard and pepper to egg mixture and beat.
Add rest of milk and vinegar.
Cook until it thickens.
Mix with 1 pint Miracle Whip.

title: shipwreck
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Place half of the slices in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add ground beef, salt, pepper, drained kidney beans and onion.
Arrange remaining potatoes on top.
Combine tomato soup and water and spoon over all.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise in half.
Mix remaining ingredients. Place 1 tablespoon cheese mixture on each half. Bake as directed on package.
Makes 20 puffs.

title: austin's 1886 lunchroom cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Saute onions, carrots and celery until tender.
Stir in flour and cornstarch.
Cook until bubbly.
Gradually add chicken stock and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add baking soda and cheese.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Season with salt, white pepper, parsley and cayenne. Garnish with paprika sprinkled on top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Add the vegetable soup mix (dry) to the other ingredients and mix well and put in refrigerator.
A great dip for vegetables as celery sticks, carrot sticks, cucumber slices, squash slices or just chips.

title: kathryn stone's sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers, onions and tomatoes. Pour boiling water over vegetables to cover.
Let stand 5 minutes then squeeze out. Place in large pot and add sugar, vinegar, salt and mustard.

Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring often as it will stick. Remove from heat and add flour mixture and stir well. Add Miracle Whip and stir well. Have canning jars and lids hot. Pour into jars and seal. Lids will seal.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in screw-top jar or small bowl.
Shake well or whip with wire whisk until ingredients are well blended and of a thick and creamy consistency.
Chill.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Shake well before using.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: egg-bread bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place bread quarter slices on bottom of dish.
Layer 2 types of cheeses and bacon.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over bread/cheese/bacon mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
If desired, before baking, top with sliced, fresh mushrooms.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter. Combine 57 sauce and water.
Pour over chicken. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until chicken is tender.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.
Skim excess fat before serving.

title: basic eggnog
directions: Put all ingredients, except nutmeg, in blender container. Cover and run on speed 5 (or high).
Pour into serving glasses; sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Drop peppers in boiling water for 4 minutes.
Mix meat, onion, sauce and Worcestershire.
Add rice; simmer 4 minutes.
Drain peppers.
Stuff with rice mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
These can be made in quantity.
After stuffing, cool, wrap individually and freeze.
When desired, cook in microwave 10 minutes on High, then add cheese and cook 5 minutes on Medium.

title: spinach, cheese and tomato pie
directions: Combine cottage cheese, milk, egg, flour, 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg and mint in blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: meat and spinach crepes
directions: Prepare crepes or bring to room temperature if refrigerated or frozen.
Remove stems from mushrooms and chop; slice caps and set aside.
In a wide frying pan over medium heat, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Add mushroom stems, onion and garlic; cook, stirring, until onion is soft.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter, sliced mushroom caps and marjoram; cook, stirring, until mushrooms are soft and juices have evaporated.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms and cook, stirring, until bubbly.
Gradually pour in milk and continue cooking and stirring until sauce boils and thickens. Remove from heat.
Add sherry, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Let cool, then season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Bake wings for about 20 minutes; drain off grease.
Mix remaining ingredients together to make sauce.
Place wings in baking dish and cover with sauce.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook to thicken up the sauce.

title: tomatoes with feta cheese
directions: Cut tomatoes in wedges.
Chop onion.
Cut cheese into 1/2-inch cubes, or break in small pieces.
Combine tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper; toss lightly.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and
milk
in
a
bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups warm water, a little
at
a
time.
Lightly flour board with 1 tablespoon of flour.
Knead the dough until it is soft but not sticky by adding
extra
flour
as needed.	Cover the bowl and let stand for 15 minutes.
Make 2-inch balls of dough and roll them into pancakes.
Heat
oil
in
Dutch
oven.
Fry pancakes until bubbles form on the dough.	Turn and fry the other side.

title: inez hemmingson's frozen cuke pickles
directions: Mix first four ingredients and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Mix the next three ingredients.
Pour over first mixture after 2 hours.
Mix well.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.

title: sizzling rice soup
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Divide rice into 8 portions.
With hands, shape and press each portion into a 2-inch patty.
Thaw pea pods by running hot water over them; cut pea pods into 1-inch lengths.
In saucepan, heat chicken broth to boiling.
Add pea pods, shrimp, bok choy and water chestnuts.
Simmer 2 minutes. Reduce heat and keep warm.

title: jazzy grapefruit chiffon pie(in honor of single delight)
directions: Combine grapefruit juice, sugar and salt; heat until sugar dissolves.
Soften gelatin in cold water; stir into hot mixture. Add egg yolks, slowly so will not curdle and mix well.
Chill until partially set; fold in egg whites, then whipped cream.
Pour into a cooled, baked shell.
Chill until firm.

title: sponge cake(serves 10)
directions: Put egg yolks in mixing bowl and add cold water.
Beat well. Add the sugar, beating constantly.
Add the
boiling water and beat until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in the flour gradually.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat the egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar and beat until soft peaks form.
Fold into yolk mixture and put into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Increase to 375°
and bake 10 minutes more.
Invert pan and cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; if watery, drain.
Add remaining ingredients and top with stuffing and butter patties.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs. Bake in a shallow baking dish at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain excess grease from meatballs.

title: not fried eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/2-inch slices, then those into inch by 4-inch strips.
Toss the strips in oil, then into a mixture of seasoned bread crumbs and Parmesan or Romano cheese, then salt and pepper.
Put them on a foil lined cookie sheet and bake them in a preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes until crisp and golden.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pour over chicken mixture.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp and artichoke bisque
directions: Boil shrimp in 6 cups water that has been lightly seasoned. Remove shrimp, reserving liquid.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Marinate chops for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chops and save marinade.
Dry chops and fry in melted margarine until brown.
Boil marinade and warm with chops.

title: piccalilly beans
directions: In saucepan, brown bologna and cook onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper meat; dust well with flour.
In small amount of shortening brown well in heavy pot (I use iron skillet).
After browning, add water to cook.
Wait until meat begins to get tender.
Then add potatoes and carrots when tender.
Add all other ingredients.

title: peanut butter jumbos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugars, peanut butter and eggs in large bowl.
Blend in baking soda and vanilla.
Add oats; mix thoroughly.
Add chips and nuts.
Make large or small cookies as desired.
The variety chips are optional to personal preference.
Makes a very big batch.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream margarine and add sugar gradually.
Beat until light and then add eggs and vanilla. Combine sifted dry ingredients and creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Add oats.
Shape dough into rolls 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap tightly in waxed paper and chill.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Bake 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: ginger sparkles
directions: Roll in ball and roll in white sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: aunt borghild's banana bread
directions: Blend together butter, egg and sugar.
Add mashed bananas. Sift together and add flour, baking soda and salt.
Finally, add milk.
Pour into loaf pan and top with chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: raw potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat peanut oil to lightly cover bottom of skillet on medium heat.
Drop by spoonfuls and flatten with a spatula.
Brown on both sides.

title: super lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cook hamburger; drain all fat off.
Slice Italian sausage. Beat eggs well with wire whip.
Begin layering in a 9 x 13-inch pan beginning with lasagna noodles.
Follow with hamburger, then Ricotta cheese, followed by spaghetti sauce.
Second layer lasagna, Italian sausage, Colby cheese, hamburger, beaten eggs and spaghetti sauce.
Last layer lasagna noodles, hamburger, Parmesan cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Make sure to make Parmesan last on your third layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stuckey's special buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: puttin' on the ritz(makes 10 dozen)
directions: Combine condensed milk and dates.
Cook until thick.
Add pecans to taste.
Put 1 teaspoon mixture on each cracker.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool.

title: mix and eat salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and eat.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend until smooth.

title: italian special sandwich
directions: Slice loaf in half, lengthwise.
Put salami, Mozzarella cheese,
pepperoni,
sliced
tomatoes,
lettuce, sweet Italian peppers and
sliced
onion	in order listed on bottom of loaf. Sprinkle with
dressing.
Cover
with
top	of loaf and cut in lengths desired.

title: baked french toast
directions: Butter a 9-inch square baking pan.
Arrange slices, overlapping to fill pan completely.
In bowl, combine eggs, milk, cream, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour over bread slices.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat until smooth. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with orange juice, beating smooth after each addition.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Ice.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: stuffed green peppers(microwave)
directions: Wash peppers, remove stems and seeds.
Place upright in 2-quart microproof casserole.
Pour water over bottom of dish and cook covered on High for 2 minutes.
Drain water; let peppers stand while preparing filling.
Crumble meat into bowl; add onion and cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir once during cooking; drain fat if any.
Stir in garlic, salt, pepper, rice and parsley and 1/2 tomato sauce.
Fill green peppers with mixture mounding on top. Replace green peppers in casserole dish and top each with remaining tomato sauce.
Cover and cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Leave a little cheese for top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: french potato sausage salad
directions: Toss cooked potatoes gently with vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Add sausage to potatoes.
Add onion.

title: ratatouille (vegetable stew)
directions: Slice eggplant 1/2 inch thick and heavily salt eggplant.
Let sit 1/2 hour to draw out moisture.
Prepare other vegetables. Rinse eggplant, dry and cube.
Saute eggplant in 1/2 oil and butter until tender and remove.
Saute onions, peppers, zucchini and tomatoes in remaining oil and butter.
Combine all ingredients and place in oiled casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Delicious as main dish or side dish.

title: marinated beef
directions: Slice frozen meat into thin strips.
Marinate in mixture of all ingredients at least 2 hours.
Cook in wok or heavy skillet quickly, just one minute.
Do not overcook.
Serve with rice and salad.

title: grandma's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil or applesauce with sugar.
Add eggs.
Measure and sift together dry ingredients into bowl, then add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 55 minutes at 300°.
Do not overbake!

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Cool.
Prick holes in top of brownies with fork.
Pour liqueur over brownies; set aside.
Prepare mousse according to directions on package. Break candy bars into small pieces.
Break up brownies.
Layer 1/2 of brownies on bottom of large bowl.
Cover with 1/2 of mousse, then 1/2 candy bars, then 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers. Refrigerate.

title: artichoke dip(variation from new mexico)
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve warm with melba toast or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: ground beef and pepper skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion until onion is tender.
Drain excess fat.
Season with pepper.
Stir in gravy; add green pepper. Simmer, uncovered, until pepper is just tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles with pea pods, if desired. Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shallow baking dish, except cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir well.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: waldorf "no fat" salad
directions: Stir together and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Blend all dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix honey, molasses and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients gradually, beating well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
(Batter will be stiff.) Place in preheated 400° oven and immediately reduce to 350°.
Bake for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Turn out on rack.

title: easy one bowl pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 20 minutes (or until well blended) in mixer.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Use Bundt pan, well-greased and floured.
This makes a lot of batter.
I also get a small loaf pan pound cake from this recipe.

title: easy mexican corn bread
directions: This does better if you cook it in glass baking dish.
Take it out as soon as it comes out of oven.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and sugar; add margarine and press into 9 x 11 baking dish.
Soften cream cheese and add 1 egg at a time as above.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool 15 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and put into desired container.
Freeze.

title: turnip slaw
directions: Using a wooden spoon, mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Chill 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie delight
directions: Combine yellow cake mix with 1/2 cup melted margarine and 1 egg.
Press into the bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sundowner
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Stir every 1 to 2 hours.
(Mixture will freeze into a slushy-type drink.) Scoop into a glass and pour 7-Up over it.
Very refreshing.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Put half of this mixture into 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Let stand in refrigerator until firm.
Keep other half out. Spread congealed layer over sour cream.
Pour remaining mixture and spread evenly.
Chill until set and cut into squares.

title: warm chocolate caramel coffee
directions: Place flavored instant coffee in cup or mug. Gradually add hot milk, stirring constantly, until instant coffee is completely dissolved. Add chocolate and caramel syrups. Stir until well blended. Top with thawed Cool Whip whipped topping, if desired. Serve immediately. Prep time: 5 minutes. Total time: 5 minutes. Makes 1 serving.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water in pan. Stir and bring to boil. Let boil approximately 10 minutes or until small amount dropped into very cold water forms a hard ball.

title: date cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add other moist ingredients.
Add flour, dates and nuts.
Add more flour if necessary.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Ice cookies when cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread in bowl and pour milk over this.
Mix.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Melt white chocolate per package directions.
In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour chocolate over cereal mixture. Stir to coat.
Spread mixture onto wax paper and cool.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put into buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° covered.

title: baked beans and wieners
directions: Cut each wiener into 3 pieces. Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sesame seed salad dressing
directions: Toast seed at 350° for ten minutes.
Combine all ingredients. Make ahead of time for flavor.
Refrigerate.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Add baking powder to flour and sift 3 times.
Blend butter and sugar with coloring added.
Prepare 1 (10 x 4-inch) tube pan by greasing with solid shortening.
Cover bottom, sides and tube with paper.
Grease paper also.

title: onion smothered pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops in oil and simmer about 10 minutes.
Place pork chops in a greased shallow baking pan.
In the same skillet, add the margarine and saut the chopped onion. The pan juices will be brown from the pork chops so your onions will also be browned from those juices already in skillet.
Add the onion soup and 1/4 cup water.
Stirring well, your sauce will have a pretty light brown color.
Pour onion-soup mixture over pork chops.
Cover and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve with Uncle Ben's brown rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into long casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: This batter will be very thin.
It makes 1 large or 3 medium loaves.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° until it springs back when touched.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Chop green pepper, red pepper, onion, garlic and hot pepper. Put marinade on meat.
Take roast and cut in small finger lengths. Put 1 tablespoon oil in skillet and roast.
Stir until all pink is gone.
Put all peppers, onions and garlic in and stir until all are tender.
Put tomato sauce and water in.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook rice and put serving size in plate.
Put beef stir-fry over.
No bread needed.
Enjoy.

title: steak in a bag
directions: Remove excess fat from steak.
Mix butter or margarine, oil, garlic, salt and pepper until blended.
Spread on all sides of steak.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Press into butter mixture on steak, coating steak well.
Place steak in brown paper grocery bag.
Fold end over and secure with staples or paper clips.

title: snowballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat with electric mixer, butter and honey.
Add all other ingredients except the powdered sugar.
Mix well with a mixing spoon.
Using your hands, shape into small 1-inch balls and place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until set and beginning to brown.
When done, remove and let cool slightly.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar until coated.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pepperoni pizza chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. Stir in the beans, pizza sauce, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, pepperoni, green pepper, pizza seasoning and salt. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until chili reaches desired thickness. Garnish with cheese, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: etta's camelback cookies(no bake)
directions: Melt butter, stir in egg, sugar and vanilla.
Mix with crackers, coconut and walnuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).

title: veal francais
directions: Cut veal into 2-inch squares and dredge in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Heat the 3 tablespoons margarine in skillet; add veal and brown on both sides.
Reduce heat to low, cover pan and cook about 20 minutes, turning 2 or 3 times.
Remove from pan and keep warm in a 200° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Drain.
Add crumbs (reserve 1 tablespoon for top), cheese, egg, salt and 2 tablespoons butter.
Put in greased casserole dish and top with rest of crumbs.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter; combine sugar and cocoa.
Add butter, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat well; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until browned, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pot pie dough
directions: Mix flour and eggs.
Add enough water to make soft dough. Roll out thin and cut.

title: italian sauce with meatballs and sausage
directions: In a large pot, saute onion in hot oil until just tender, then add garlic.
Stir in tomato paste and two cans of water.
Add salt, pepper, sweet basil, oregano and parsley if you like.
Bring to a low boil, constantly stirring.
Add tomatoes and the 1 can of water.
Bring to a slow boil.*
Add sausage and meatballs.
Cook on low for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: shrewsbury (pound) cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs to sugar mixture, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder. Alternating with flour mixture, add milk, vanilla and salt to batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add cheese and relish. Heat slowly until cheese melts and flavors blend.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: french fruit cake
directions: Combine raisins, 2 cups water and 1/2 cup sugar; boil for 15 minutes.
Drain raisins.
Add enough hot water to raisin water to make 2 cups.
Into hot water, add brown sugar, shortening and salt; mix.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake slowly at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.
Done when cake pulls away from sides of pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice and drain.
Place in buttered baking dish, add salt and milk.
Bake 1 1/2 hours with cover on dish at 300°.
Stir occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 to 1 hour longer.
Do not stir after adding last ingredients.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Steam or boil potatoes until done.
Peel skins while still slightly warm and cut into thin slices.
Place potatoes into mixing bowl.
Add chives, onions, bacon, chicken broth, mayonnaise, French dressing and wine vinegar.
Mix well and let stand for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: golden cheddar chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Split chicken breasts in half and arrange in one layer in greased baking dish.

title: raw cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, onions, milk and seasonings until smooth. Break cauliflower into small pieces and add with celery salt and peas to mayonnaise mixture.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 12 x 2 1/2-inch pan. Pour in the pineapple and cherries.
Spread coconut over all. Sprinkle in cake mix.
Spread with pecans.
Spoon over the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coated pecan halves
directions: Mix egg white and pecans until sticky.
Add sugar and cinnamon; stir well.
Place in ungreased baking sheet and bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: summer delight chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening and gradually add sugar.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and measure.
Sift again, adding cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to butter mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: korean sauce for chicken
directions: Marinate chicken no more than 12 hours.
Chicken can be baked, fried or barbecued.

title: peanut chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla, beat until fluffy.
Blend in peanut butter.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Stir in peanuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons or No. 100 scoop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Yields 7 to 8 dozen.

title: linguine with crab
directions: Melt butter in skillet, add onions, mushrooms and ginger when foaming.
Add half and half and cream cheese.
Increase heat and cook 2 to 3 minutes until mixture begins to thicken. Add crab, peppers and salt.
Cook crab until hot, stir as little as possible.
Have pasta ready as soon as sauce is done!

title: sweet potatoes cakes
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Gradually fold in sweet potatoes.
Pour into greased 9 X 13 aluminum pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry popover pancake
directions: Place butter in 9-inch glass pie plate; place in 200° oven until butter melts. In a medium bowl, beat flour, milk and eggs until well blended. Pour mixture over melted butter; do not stir. Drop chocolate chips evenly over flour mixture. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges of pancake are puffed and a deep golden brown.

title: chewy macaroon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg yolks and salt together. Add sugar,
cup
at
a time, until blended.
Beat in milk, butter, lemon juice and extracts.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold beaten egg whites and coconut into egg yolk mixture.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake on baking sheet for 30 minutes or until knife inserted near rim comes out clean.
Cool.

title: beans and rice salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Cook rice according to package, omitting salt if desired. Rinse with cold water; drain.
Combine rice and 1/4 cup salad dressing, stirring well.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Spoon rice onto individual lettuce-lined plates.
Spoon bean mixture over rice. Top with cheese, green onions, tomato and, if desired, sour cream. Makes 4 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place raw meat on bottom of a pan.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Spread Tater Tots evenly on top of hamburger.
On top of that, add soups (do not dilute soups).
Cover with foil; place in a 350° preheated oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook hamburger, bacon and onion; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook for 1/2 hour.
Serve and enjoy!

title: catalina chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch cubes. Saute in 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium heat. Stir occasionally. Cook until chicken is firm but not browned. Add Catalina salad dressing and hot sauce (if desired) to pan. Stir to coat chicken evenly. Continue to stir until dressing thickens and no longer remains in the bottom of pan.

title: crescents
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add nuts.
Shape into crescent shaped cookies. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
They will be only lightly brown.
Cool. Roll in powdered sugar (more than the 4 tablespoons that went into the batter).

title: circus train cookies
directions: To assemble cookies, pipe strip of frosting along outer edge of one (2-inch) side of 1 graham cracker.

Press 2-inch edge of second graham cracker into frosted edge to form 3 x 2-inch rectangle. Using writing tip, pipe frosting around outer edge of rectangle. Place 1 animal cracker lengthwise in center of rectangle.
Pipe 3 vertical lines resembling cage bars.
Attach ring candy one to each lower corner to resemble wheels.
Arrange cookies side by side to form train of 11 cookies.

title: * easy skillet spaghetti *
directions: In skillet over medium coals, brown ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until spaghetti is tender, stirring frequently. Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Blend everything in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat for 1 minute.
Serve hot or cold.
Great with ice cream.

title: toasted mushroom sandwiches
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Drain and set aside.
Combine cream cheese and mushroom soup in a small bowl. Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add sauteed mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and next three ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Set aside.

title: easy fruit pies
directions: Soften cream cheese and add Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and whipped topping.
Mix together and pour into crusts.
Chill.
Top with chilled fruit pie filling (cherry, blueberry or strawberry). Yield:
2 pies.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix milk, butter and powdered sugar.
Add coconut and walnuts. Make into small balls and chill.
Melt chocolate in double boiler; place toothpicks in the chilled balls and dip in the chocolate; chill and re-dip. Remove toothpick and let chocolate set.

title: midnight mints
directions: Bottom layer: Combine butter, cocoa and sugar in saucepan and bring slowly to a boil. Stir in egg to thicken. Remove from heat and add crumbs, nuts and coconut. Pack very firmly into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar with butter, stirring constantly.
When a golden brown, add chopped or whole nuts and then pour into hot, buttered pan.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer rhubarb, sugar, jello and marshmallows.
Press down.
Mix cake according to directions. Pour over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. When cool, turn upside down on cookie sheet or tray.

title: pork and rice bombay
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large skillet over medium heat saute onion, green pepper and garlic in 1 tablespoon of the oil for 3 minutes.
Add rice.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes or until rice is clear and golden.
Add mushrooms, broth, tomato sauce, water, curry powder and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Put into a 2 1/2-quart oblong baking dish; set aside.
In the skillet over medium-high heat, brown chops on both sides in remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Arrange on top of rice.
Cover tightly and bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until rice and chops are tender. Garnish with tomatoes and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Serve as a delightful conclusion to any meal.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add beaten egg and stir until mixed.
Add the rhubarb and pour into pie plate lined with pastry. Dot with small amount of butter or margarine if desired.
Cover with top crust, fastening edges securely.
Make a few slits on top or prick the center with a fork for air and steam to escape. Bake in 400° to 425° oven for about 35 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan caramel pie
directions: Melt caramels, butter and water in microwave. Add other ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: herb bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and mix well.
Add egg, nutmeg, sage, celery seed and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Add flour to make a soft dough; knead in more flour as needed, 5 to 8 minutes on floured surface.
Let rise in greased bowl about 90 minutes.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into rounded loaf.
Place in greased 8-inch pie pan.
Let rise until doubled. Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
To check doneness, tap it with a fingertip.
Bread should have a "hollow" sound when tapped. Cool on wire rack until ready to serve to prevent bottom from "sweating."

title: pear relish
directions: Wash, peel and core pears. Chop pears, peppers, celery and onions in food processor. Add sugar, salt, allspice and vinegar. Mix well and let set overnight. Heat to boiling point. Boil a little bit. Pack in hot jars. Process 20 minutes in boiling bath.

title: sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage and onion over low heat until brown.
Drain fat. Add cheese, whole egg, Tabasco sauce, salt and parsley.
Set aside.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo with sugar. Add eggs one at a time and vanilla flavoring. Alternate with milk and vanilla wafers.	Add coconut and pecans. Cook 90 minutes at 275°. Better check for doneness earlier!

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar, Kool-Aid and water.
Add pineapple juice and ginger ale.
