Recipe makes enough punch for 25 people.
May be doubled and tripled for large groups.

title: aunt cele's fruit & nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar. Add beaten eggs. Mix dry ingredients with milk, add fruits and nuts. Combining all well. Refrigerate several hours. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix well, then add the flour, crushed cornflakes, baking soda, oatmeal and coconut.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by a teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Serves 36.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease and flour bottom only of 1 (9 x 5-inch) or 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
In large bowl, beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add bananas, sour cream and eggs; blend well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Put sugar, eggs and oil in mixer and mix.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add vanilla, pecans, apple and first mixture.
Mix well in large bowl.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot slaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, salt, pepper, sugar, bell pepper, pimento and mustard.
Heat vinegar, oil and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Heat until tender.

title: pork with tangy mustard sauce
directions: Rub roast with oil. Combine ground mustard, garlic powder and ginger; rub over roast. Place in a large resealable plastic bag or covered container. Refrigerate overnight. Grill roast, covered, over indirect heat for 60 minutes. Combine horseradish mustard and preserves. Continue grilling 15 to 20 minutes, basting with sauce twice or until heat meat thermometer reads 160° to 170°. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing. Heat remaining sauce to serve with roast.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil the unopened can of condensed milk in covered saucepan of water for 3 hours, keeping water over can of milk.
Let cool; pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook frozen mixed vegetables until tender-crisp.
Drain well and cool.
Cook sugar, vinegar and mustard until slightly thick. Cool.
Combine all the vegetables.
Pour cooled sauce over vegetables.
Mix well and chill thoroughly.

title: fried okra
directions: Slice okra; place in bowl and cover with milk and let stand for 30 minutes; drain.
Put cornmeal and pepper in a bag.
Add okra; shake, then fry.
Turn only once during frying.
Drain on paper towel.
Salt.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Let sugar and milk come to a boil.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme and add vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut into squares.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients like pie crust until soft.
(Punch dough as much as you like, hence the name "Aggression Cookies.")
Flatten 1-inch balls of dough on ungreased pan.
Press flat using bottom of drinking glass dipped in white, granulated sugar.
Bake in moderate oven at 300° to 325° about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.
Scrumptious!!

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Crumble crackers in buttered casserole dish.
Cut asparagus and place on crackers.
Pour asparagus juice over top.
Slice eggs and place on top of asparagus.
Cut 1/2 of pimentos and place over eggs.
Spread soup.
Add remaining pimentos and pimento juice. Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In large skillet, cook beef, onion, green peppers and garlic until tender.
Pour off fat.
Add other ingredients; bring to boil.
Cover pan; cook over low heat 15 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: happiness cake
directions: Dish out with a large spoon, like a pudding, and garnish with fresh apple slices dipped in lemon juice and cinnamon sugar.

title: chocolate mounds
directions: Mix powdered sugar, milk, margarine, coconut and pecans together; form
into
balls
and
place
on wax paper.
Put in refrigerator
to chill overnight.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in
a
double
boiler.
Keep	burner	on
low heat while dipping coconut
balls
and place them on wax paper with sides not touching.
Keep
them
in a cool place in a room until the chocolate has set.

title: good coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high for 15 seconds.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: morning glory
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in 8 x 8 -inch pan and place in the refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, place in a 350° oven for approximately 40 minutes.
Other items can be added to this if you wish, such as onion, peppers, olives; use your imagination and enjoy.

title: rigatoni with cheese and sausage
directions: Bake sausage at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Slice thin and set aside.
Saute onions and garlic in butter until soft, but not brown.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk; cook and stir constantly over medium heat until mixture begins to boil.
Add 1 cup sharp cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend until cheese is melted.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beating well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon; add to first mixture.
Stir in pineapple and bananas.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: maple nut pie
directions: Bring sweetened condensed milk and maple syrup to a gentle boil in heavy saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Mixture will stick.
Remove from heat and stir in maple extract.
Pour into pie crust.
Cool completely.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter and oleo.
Mix together with all ingredients.
Make into small balls and flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add
remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan
at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Ice with Vanilla Cream Cheese Icing.

title: bear's bananas
directions: In a skillet, heat butter and brown sugar for 5 minutes, or until sugar is melted and begins to caramelize.
Add the liqueur and stir.
Add the bananas and cook for about 1 minute - just enough to heat through - don't let them get mushy!	Serve immediately, either by themselves or with ice cream.

title: fruit cake crunch
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Mix pie filling and cake mix.
Pour into dish; melt 1 stick of butter and pour over top of pie filling/cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown around edge.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each one. Beat in flour. Add flavoring and pecans. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add soup, sour cream and half of cheese.
Add onions and pour over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper and mix well. Pour in buttered dish; cook for 30 minutes at 350° and then add rest of cheese and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake for another 10 minutes.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Cut all ingredients very coarsely.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling and simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: wade's buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter; add cumin, red pepper and paprika.
Set aside.
Cut tips from wings, then cut remainder in half.
Spray two large broiling pans with nonstick cooking spray. Place wings on rack.
Bake on one side about 40 minutes, then turn and brown on second side.
Remove from oven and brush both sides with butter mixture.
Bake until crisp.

title: hot pastrami sandwich
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Add meat; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
For each sandwich, spread bottom half of roll with mustard; cover with meat mixture and cheese spread.
Broil until cheese spread begins to melt.
Serve with top half of roll, 4 sandwiches.
Prep time: 10 minutes. Cooking time: 3 minutes.

title: creamed irish whiskey
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender for 3 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, pimentos, chilies and olives until smooth. Spread on flour tortillas and roll.
Let chill for 6 to 8 hours and cut into bite size pieces.
Makes excellent finger snacks.

title: barbecue wings
directions: Brown chicken wings in half of the oil.
Use the other half of oil and cook onions until tender.
Combine all other ingredients in large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Let simmer for 30 minutes. Then pour over wings in a large pan and bake 1 hour in 350° oven, until meat is very tender.

title: cheesy bacon baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and pat dry.
Pierce with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 54 to 65 minutes or until soft.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour on baking sheet.
Bake in a 250 degree oven for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: potato-mushroom bake(serves 4)
directions: In a buttered, shallow baking dish, layer potatoes, onion and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour cream over top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 30 minutes longer.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch pan for approximately 25 minutes.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
This may be made and refrigerated until ready to cook.

title: coralie's red jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in other ingredients and refrigerate until firmly set (jello will be quite stiff).

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
(Take away 1 cup for crumbs on top of cake.
To this part, add butter and cinnamon.) Beat the eggs in a measuring cup; fill cup with milk.
Beat in the dry ingredients until smooth.
Put into pan; put crumbs on top. Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put 3 tablespoons of mixture in center of each tortilla and spread.
Roll up and chill.
Cut into slices.
Serve with taco sauce for dipping.

title: italian bake
directions: Boil the noodles until tender, then drain well.
Brown the ground beef and onion; drain.
Add the Hunt's sauce and the diced tomatoes.
Layer each ingredient in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: talerini
directions: Saute onions, garlic, celery and pepper in a little olive or salad oil.
When soft, but not brown, add ground beef and toss until it loses its color and separates.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, corn, olives, salt, red pepper and Worcestershire to taste. Let this simmer until well blended.
Add a little water if necessary.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salt water 15 minutes.
In a greased casserole or earthenware dish, layer spaghetti, grated cheese and meat mixture.
Repeat layers and put in moderate oven for about 30 minutes.
Pass freshly grated Parmesan cheese with the dish.
This may be prepared 24 hours before needed and put in refrigerator to be heated when needed.
Serves 12.

title: holiday hot punch
directions: In a 30-cup coffeemaker, pour the cranberry juice and apple juice together.

In coffee basket, place brown sugar, salt, cinnamon sticks and cloves. Run coffeemaker through the regular cycle (as if making coffee) or just once in a percolator according to how strong a spice taste you want.
Recipe may be halved for smaller gatherings.
Makes 30 cups.

title: coconut-peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together peanut butter, butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Add coconut.
Spread in greased 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 to 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: creamed corned scallops casserole
directions: Spread spinach leaves on bottom of a 6 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Spread across chopped scallops to 1-inch thickness.
Season with condiments of your own choice; i.e., pepper, garlic powder, Italian spices and seasonings, garlic salt, etc.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut lettuce as for salad.
Cut cauliflower into florets.
Slice onion into rings.
Fry bacon and break into pieces.
Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Parmesan cheese.
When ready to serve, add dressing to salad.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook spinach in butter.
Drain well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly baked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, until top is lightly brown.

title: crab and pasta
directions: Combine all of the preceding and heat on top of stove.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Imitation crab works well.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chocolate cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Beat together confectioners sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Drop by spoonful over chocolate cake mixture (don't swirl).
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal-brownie pie
directions: With electric mixer: beat together all ingredients in a large mixing bowl, except oats and nuts. Stir oatmeal and nuts into beaten mixture and pour into prebaked pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool completely and serve at room temperature with a dollop of whipped topping on each serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken-cabbage stir-fry
directions: Partly brown diced chicken in large skillet.
Shred cabbage and stir in with chicken.
Season to taste with garlic powder, whole cumin seed, basil, minced onion and oregano.
Use whole celery seed for salt flavor.
Use crushed red pepper to make spicy.
Put top on skillet and let cook 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Goes well with little red potatoes and Jiffy cornbread. Serves 2 to 4 persons.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugars, dressing and vanilla with electric mixer. Add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of the batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Make frosting first and chill.
Mix first 4 ingredients and chill while cake is baking.
Add Cool Whip and ready to frost.

title: macadamia cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, combine brown and white sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Continue beating and scraping bowl often, until well mixed.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and white chocolate by hand. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from pan.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, onion and celery in small amount of water (for approximately 5 minutes).
In separate pan, put in cream of mushroom soup using 3/4 can of water.
Be sure to mix water in a little at a time to keep smooth.
Heat.
Pour heated cream of mushroom soup over hot broccoli mixture.
Add Cheez Whiz and margarine.
Mix until melted.
Add rice and stir.
Put in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until liquid has been absorbed by rice.

title: danish bakeless cake
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add sugar and egg yolks creamed together.
Beat well and let come to a boil.
Remove from stove. Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
On bottom of pan or dish, place a layer of wafers, then a layer of custard mixture.
Make 3 layers of wafers and 2 of custard mixture.
Put in refrigerator for about 12 hours or longer.
Whip 1 pint of whipping cream and sweeten to taste.
Prepared topping may be used.
Put topping on servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix filling in order given.
Pour into crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake an additional 40 or 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
If necessary, cover the edge of crust with foil to prevent crust browning too much.
Cool.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a long cake pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This cake is real chewy.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Drain hearts and break up into pieces.
Add mayo and cheese. Pour into ungreased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Recipe may be doubled and may be frozen too! This doesn't taste anything like artichokes.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers and onion in bowl. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Mix well and let stand in refrigerator.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Saute onion in butter/margarine until tender.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, marjoram and mustard.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Stir in bouillon cube.
Gradually add milk and cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and stir until melted.
Pour sauce over broccoli in greased ovenproof casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until browned.

title: chimichangas
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan heat 2 tablespoons corn oil over medium heat.
Add meat and onion.
Cook, stirring, 5 minutes or until browned.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Stirring frequently, cook 12 minutes, or until no liquid remains.
Cool.
Soften tortillas according to package directions.
Spoon 3 to 4 tablespoons meat mixture on lower half of each tortilla, near edge. Fold 2 opposite sides toward center.
Roll up from bottom.
Pour about 1 pint corn oil into a heavy skillet to depth of 1/2-inch, filling not more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat.
Carefully add chimichangas, seam side down, a few at a time.
Fry, turning once, 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel. Top with remaining ingredients.
You may use chicken or beef in place of the pork.

title: parslied potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and butter in medium size frying pan.
Heat slowly until butter melts.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; toss lightly.
Saute slowly, stirring several times, 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Stir in parsley.

title: ravioli in walnut cream sauce
directions: In a large pot of boiling, salted water, cook the ravioli according to package directions just until tender, but still firm, about 7 minutes.
Place the walnuts in a food processor.
Process until they are finely ground.

title: french mushroom rice casserole
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine soup and butter. Stir well and pour in pan.
Drain mushrooms and water chestnuts. Save liquid.
Add water to liquid to equal 1 1/3 cups.
Add mushrooms, water chestnuts, liquid and rice to pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves eight.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, onion soup and preserves well in a small bowl.
Lay chicken out in a single layer in a Pam sprayed baking dish.
Pour salad dressing mixture over chicken and cover with foil.
Bake one hour at 300°.
Remove foil; baste chicken and cook uncovered 1 hour longer.

title: frosty
directions: Blend milk and Nestles Quik for 10 seconds on high speed in blender.
Pulse in the ice cream until barely mixed.
Mixture should be very thick.
Freeze for at least one hour before serving.

title: breaded veal cutlets(oven prepared)
directions: Dip cutlets in egg and crumbs.
Season.
Brown in drippings on top of stove to brown meat.
Place in casserole or baking dish. Add water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over veal; cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: mini-meat loaf dinner
directions: Place margarine in custard cup.
Microwave uncovered on High (100%) until melted; 30 to 45 seconds.
Stir in dill weed.
Cut potato lengthwise into fourths.
Brush cut sides with margarine mixture.
Arrange, cut sides up, on 9-inch plate.
Wrap corn in microwavable paper towel; place on plate next to potato.
Microwave uncovered on High (100%) until hot, 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and 1 teaspoon of the soup mix; shape into loaf.
Place meat loaf on plate with corn and potato; sprinkle with remaining soup mix.
Cover plate with microwavable paper towel and microwave until beef is no longer pink inside, 6 to 7 minutes.

title: crowd pleasing potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes whole with bay leaf. Let cool and then peel. Grate potatoes and cheese. Cut up green onions into small pieces. Mix all ingredients. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all together and place in shallow pan with lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove lid last 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Double recipe, double cooking time.

title: banana smoothies
directions: Cut bananas into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap pieces in clear plastic or foil.
Freeze several hours until firm.
Measure milk into blender.
Add yogurt.
Measure in sugar and vanilla.
Put in half of the banana pieces, cover and blend until well mixed.
Add remainder; cover and blend until smooth.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand for 20 minutes. Cream the shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add beaten eggs, then add to oatmeal mixture.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt, then add to oatmeal mixture.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, then spread the topping while cake is warm.

title: sour cream gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan. Beat eggs.
Add sour cream, molasses and ginger.
When smooth, sift in dry ingredients. Beat again.
When smooth, stir in butter. Pour into pan. Bake 25 minutes. Serve warm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Simmer together with olive oil just a bit; add salt, pepper and a dash of sugar.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Lightly brown the onion and celery in butter. Add the flour and salt and mix thoroughly. Remove from heat.
Add the tuna and milk.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat until hot, but do not let it boil.
Serve with crackers.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 4 tablespoons sugar and pat into a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400°
for 8 minutes; cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in balls the size of silver dollars.
Dip fork in water or flour and mash balls with fork.
Bake at 350°
until brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain well.
Add special sauce and cumin to mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook rice and set aside.
Combine meat mixture and rice.
Mix well and serve.

title: fruity bake
directions: Put oats, figs, dates and raisins in food processor and grind. Put in bowl and add lime juice to moisten.

title: java sticks
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Beat in coffee, flour and pecans.
Roll into finger shapes and place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let sticks cool. Dip in melted chocolate.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Let hash browns thaw in bag.
Combine all ingredients and mix together.
Place in a buttered casserole or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
I bake half of this and freeze half to bake at a later date.

title: calico tea
directions: In medium bowl, mix all ingredients.
Spoon into jar and cover tightly.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon.
Remove from pan and saute onion, green pepper and celery in bacon grease.
Drain sauteed vegetables.
Crumble bacon and combine with sauteed vegetables, tomato soup, almonds, mushrooms and green beans.
Put in a 2-quart casserole and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bromwoods spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
(May defrost and cook in microwave.)
Add flour to slightly beaten eggs and beat until smooth.
Add cottage cheese, spinach and Cheddar cheese.
Spread into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: faster candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 3 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes and stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Red cinnamons and/or coconut can be added for taste or festivity.

title: pasta with chicken
directions: Saute chicken breasts in wok in 2 tablespoons oil until almost done.
Add peppers and garlic to chicken and cook.
Add sauce, olives, chicken broth, rosemary and thyme; mix.
Add cooked pasta, mix and heat through.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of oblong cake pan.
Take spoon and dip filling onto pineapple, then spread as evenly as possible. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pineapple and cherry pie filling. Slice margarine over dry cake mix.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°. Watch to make sure butter doesn't get too brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour half of mixture in each crust.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Keep cold until ready to serve.

title: pickle pinwheels
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Remove seed.
Mix together lime and 8 1/2 quarts water.
Add cucumber rings and put into two 1-gallon jars.
Soak 24 hours.
Drain and wash well in two waters.
Cover cucumber rings with water and soak 3 hours.
Mix together 1 cup vinegar, 1 tablespoon alum and 3 tablespoons red food coloring.
Add enough water and cover cucumbers.
Simmer 2 hours.
Drain; discard water.
Mix together remaining ingredients and heat.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let sit 24 hours.
Drain and reheat liquid (do not boil).
Pour over cucumbers.
Put lid on for steam and let sit for 24 hours.
Heat liquid and cucumbers together and put in jars and seal.

title: lemon squares 1
directions: Melt margarine.
Add confectioners sugar and 1 cup flour. Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs. Add sugar, flour, baking powder and lemon juice.
Spread over hot crust and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with applesauce.
Add soda in boiling water.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients well; place in well-greased baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350° until browned.

title: golden nugget cookies
directions: Sift nutmeg with flour.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and carrots.
Blend in flour.	drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes at 400.
Cool.

title: fruit cobbler - two in one(apple and peach)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping, press remaining in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add apple pie filling at one end of the pan and peach pie filling at the other end of the pan.
Put reserved batter on top in blobs; stretch out.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes on middle rack.
Eat from what half you desire.
Other fruits may be used.

title: ham rolls
directions: Split rolls.
Mix all ingredients together and spread on rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm. Freezes well.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture with buttermilk.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts, cherries and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Glaze with confectioners' sugar icing.

title: chow-chow relish
directions: Wash all vegetables. Peel onion and remove pepper seeds. Chop all vegetables and measure. Dissolve salt in water. Pour over vegetables and let stand 1 hour. Drain and taste. If too salty, rinse again. Mix vegetables with sugar, mustard seeds and vinegar. Simmer 20 minutes, then bring to a full boil. Pack boiling hot into jars and seal at once.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 large loaf.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sweet-sour cucumbers
directions: About 1 hour before serving or up to 2 days ahead, in large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: zucchini torte
directions: Mix together and place in a greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: good and easy corn casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until slightly browned on top.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Cut Velveeta into quarters and put into crock-pot.
Add cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Place crock-pot on high.
Brown in a skillet the hamburger and sausage.
Drain and pour into crock-pot.
Cook on high for 30 to 45 minutes or until all cheese has melted, stirring occasionally.
Turn on low and enjoy with tostado chips.

title: chicken-corn soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts with salt and pepper in 3 quarts water until tender.
Remove, cool and chop chicken.
Strain broth.

title: lemonade salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello and dissolve.
Add lemonade; let set until partially jelled.
Add fruit, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Mix the brownie mix, eggs, water and oil together; place in a well-greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies start to pull away from pan.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine shredded cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, 1/4 cup margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in potatoes.
Turn into baking dish.
Toss together corn flakes and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until casserole is golden brown and potatoes are tender.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 4 tablespoons sugar, powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 sticks softened butter.
Beat until smooth; spread over crumbs.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix eggs and milk; add baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Turn dough out and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Fry until golden brown.

title: brownie alaska
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate, remove from heat and blend in sugar.
Add eggs and water; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in greased 7 x 11-inch pan for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 8 squares.
Place on baking sheet.
Cut each pint carton of ice cream into 4 blocks.
Place one on each brownie and freeze (about 2 hours).

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Brown onion and celery in butter until soft and golden. Combine remaining ingredients and bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs before baking.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour and mayonnaise, then add milk and baking powder. Drop into well-greased muffin tins.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 6 to 9 biscuits.

title: "two alarm" chili
directions: Sear meat in skillet with onions and garlic.
When meat is thoroughly seared, put in tomato sauce, add some water to cover meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover with half an inch of water and stir well. Simmer at least 1 1/2 hours (or longer), stirring regularly.
Towards the end of cooking time, skim the grease, add flour mixed with warm water to thicken. Serves 6.

title: man's meal
directions: Melt shortening in a skillet.
Add meat.
Brown meat, stirring with a fork.
Add chili and water.
Mix well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook rigatoni according to directions on package.
Drain.
Return to pot.
Add butter and meat mixture. Mix well.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until thick as desired.

title: extremely easy bean dip
directions: In a pie plate, cut up cream cheese.
Spoon chilies over cream cheese.
Spoon chili with beans over top.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Microwave until bubbly on High (3 to 5 minutes).
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Tastes just like meat loaf, but no hamburger.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: homemade sauerkraut
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand for 24 hours.
Chop cabbage, clean jars and lids real hot.
Pack cabbage in jars. Pour warm solution over cabbage and seal.

title: tangy cabbage salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Chill well.
Yield: about 12 servings.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix together and pour into frozed pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Boil altogether for 5 to 7 minutes.
Spread over cake and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: confetti fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over low heat. Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in condensed milk, butter and vanilla.
Blend until butter is mixed with chocolate. Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture immediately into lightly oiled 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle confetti sprinkles on top of fudge. Cool at room temperature.
Cut into even squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown the chicken pieces.
Dip in flour and oil.
Put in casserole. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheeses until well blended.
Add other ingredients except pecans; mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap and chill for 24 hours.
Serve.
Yields a 1 1/2 pound ball.

title: deoris sweet potatoes
directions: Combine and place in a casserole dish the first 6 ingredients. Top with the remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma taylor's chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla for about 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until crust forms on pie.

title: twenty minute chocolate cake and icing
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Boil next 3 ingredients, margarine, cocoa and water.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and flour mixture.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Five minutes before cake is done, make icing.

title: prime rib with mustard sauce
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Rub meat with garlic and sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Place meat in uncovered roasting pan, fat side up.
Cook 30 minutes or until browned.
Reduce temperature to 325° and cook until meat is tender, allowing 30 minutes per pound for medium-well and 18 minutes per pound for rare meat.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Stir in pizza sauce.
Cut biscuit into quarters, fold into ground beef mixture.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: microwave broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in crackers; reserve 1/4 of this for topping.
Precook and thaw broccoli in microwave (in boxes with ends open, 4 minutes each box).
Mix together broccoli, soup and cracker/butter mixture.
Put remaining crackers on top.
Microwave 5 minutes on High.

title: melissa's mud cake and icing
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and while hot, spread on marshmallow cream.
Let cool and then put on icing.

title: franks and macaroni
directions: Saute frankfurter slices, onions and green pepper in margarine. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serves four.

title: grandma's delight
directions: In saucepan, melt marshmallows, cream and pineapple slowly. When melted, add nuts and chopped cherries.
This will be thick. Line a big baking or refrigerator dish with some of the crumbs; add remaining filling and cover with more crumbs but not over 1/4-inch thick or dessert will be dry.
Take second jar of cherries that have been drained and left whole and put on top of crumbs.

title: more
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Layer noodles and sauce twice.
Grate Velveeta cheese over top of casserole.
Bake for 25 minutes or until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: holiday party dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except fresh vegetables. Mix well.
Cover; chill.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with additional green onion, if desired.
Serve with vegetables. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: no fry doughnuts
directions: In a large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.

Add milk, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour. Blend for 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in remaining flour until smooth, scraping side of bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 50 to 60 minutes. Turn dough onto well floured cloth covered board. Roll around lightly to cover with flour.
(Dough will be soft to handle.) With floured stockinet covered rolling pin, gently roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch doughnut (or cut both ends of a can out about 2 1/2-inch in diameter and use about a 1-inch thick cutter for the centers).
Lift doughnuts carefully with a spatula and place 2-inches apart on a greased baking sheet. Brush doughnuts with melted butter. Cover and let rise about 20 minutes or doubled in bulk.
Heat oven to 425° and bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately brush with melted butter and shake in cinnamon/sugar, or if desired, spread with Creamy Glaze or Chocolate Glaze.

title: air guard baked bean recipe
directions: Combine above ingredients and add cut up ham or bacon. Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring twice during baking.

title: chef bramons pioneer beef stew
directions: Saute salt pork, set aside.
Brown beef in butter.
Add chopped onion and garlic.
Add flour (make a paste with a little warm water).
Add tomato puree and stock.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Add pearl onions (optional), mushrooms and salt pork.
Let simmer 15 minutes.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Brown chicken slightly in fat.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add paprika, garlic and water.
Arrange pepper rings and tomatoes on top.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Mix flour to paste with a little sour cream, then add to remaining cream.
Then pour over the chicken.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Serve with noodles.

title: chocolaty butterscotch treats
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter together in large saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add Cocoa Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.

title: beaufort stew(great for a crowd!)
directions: Boil water.
Add salt and pepper; add sausage and corn.
Bring to a boil again.
Add shrimp; cover and let boil about 5 minutes. Remove from heat; let stand about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: glazed carrots with lemon juice
directions: Scrape carrots; cut into fourths, lengthwise.
Place carrots in heavy skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over low heat, turning frequently, until carrots are tender and glazed.
